19.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real-estate%20company%20estimated%20city-%20and%20state-level%20childcare%20costs%20from%202009%20to%202022%20for%20the%20typical%20American%20family%20with%201.94%20children%20by%20analyzing%20data%20from%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Bureau%20of%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%20and%20advocacy%20group%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.childcareaware.org%2Fcatalyzing-growth-using-data-to-change-child-care-2022%2F%23PriceofCare%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EChild%20Care%20Aware%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Zillow%E2%80%99s%20analysis%2C%20in%2031%20of%20the%20largest%2050%20US%20metropolitan%20areas%20with%20available%20childcare%20cost%20data%2C%20families%20looking%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20can%20expect%20to%20spend%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20mortgage%20and%20childcare%20costs.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20areas%20are%20even%20costlier%2C%20with%20parents%20in%20cities%20like%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20San%20Diego%20needing%20to%20dedicate%20as%20much%20as%20121%25%20and%20113%25%2C%20respectively.%20(In%20those%20areas%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20buying%20a%20typical%20home%20and%20childcare%20is%20so%20big%20relative%20to%20the%20median%20income%20that%20Zillow's%20calculation%20results%20in%20figures%20over%20100%25.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZillow%20determined%20that%20a%20family%20earning%20a%20median%20household%20income%20of%20%246%2C640%20per%20month%20can%20expect%20to%20allocate%20%241%2C984%20of%20that%20to%20childcare.%20If%20the%20family%20purchased%20a%20house%20at%20a%206.61%25%20interest%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20the%20rate%20in%20early%20January%2C%20when%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%20released%20its%20latest%20data%20on%20childcare%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20made%20a%2010%25%20down%20payment%2C%20their%20monthly%20mortgage%20would%20amount%20to%20%241%2C973.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20just%20%242%2C683%20for%20additional%20expenses%20like%20food%2C%20transp