n-hunter-explained-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBurisma%20Holdings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20new%20court%20filings.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmirnov%2C%20an%20ex-FBI%20informant%2C%20was%20arrested%20last%20week%2C%20and%20federal%20prosecutors%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fsco-weiss%2Fpr%2Fgrand-jury-returns-indictment-charging-fbi-confidential-human-source-felony-false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindicted%3C%2Fa%3E%20him%20on%20charges%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20lying%20to%20officials%20and%20falsifying%20records%20related%20to%20his%20claims%20that%20both%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Hunter%20Biden%20each%20accepted%20%245%20million%20dollar%20bribes%20from%20Burisma%20Holdings%20officials%20to%20protect%20the%20company%20and%20its%20executives%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20all%20kinds%20of%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP%20has%20touted%20Smirnov%20as%20a%20star%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-republicans-biden-impeachment-fbi-indictment-hunter-bribes-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bwhistleblower%26quot%3B%20witness%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20impeach%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20White%20House%20and%20lawyers%20for%20Smirnov%20and%20Hunter%20Biden%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmirnov%20first%20claimed%20that%20the%20Bidens%20accepted%20bribes%20in%20reports%20to%20his%20FBI%20handler%20in%20June%202020.%20His%20allegations%20were%20based%20on%20several%20purported%20meetings%20he%20had%20with%20officials%20from%20Burisma%20Holdings.%20In%20the%20reported%20meetings%2C%20Smirnov%20claimed%20Burisma%20officials%20said%20the%20bribes%20to%20the%20Bidens%20would%20enable%20Hunter%20Biden%20to%20quash%2C%20through%20his%20father%2C%20a%20criminal%20investigation%20that%20the%20then-Ukrainian%20Prosecutor%20General%20was%20conducting%20into%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20events%20Smirnov%20recounted%20to%20his%20FBI%20handler%20in%20June%202020%20%26quot%3Bwere%20fabrications%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20alleged%20in%20the%20pre-trial%20detention%20memo%20filed%20Tuesday%2C%20which%20states%20Smirnov%20only%20had%20contact%20with%20Burisma%20executives%20after%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Obama-Biden%20administration%20and%20after%20the%20then-Ukrainian%20Prosecutor%20General%20had%20been%20fired%20in%20February%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20when%20Public%20Official%201%20had%20no%20ability%20to%20influence%20US%20policy%20and%20when%20the%20Prosecutor%20General%20was%20no%20longer%20in%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20memo%20reads.%20%26quot%3BIn%20short%2C%20Smirnov%20transformed%20his%20routine%20and%20unextraordinary%20business%20contacts%20with%20Burisma%20in%202017%20and%20later%20into%20bribery%20allegations%20against%20Public%20Official%201%2C%20the%20presumptive%20nominee%20of%20one%20of%20the%20two%20major%20political%20parties%20for%20President%2C%20after%20expressing%20bias%20against%20Public%20Official%201%20and%20his%20candidacy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20February%2014%20arrest%20at%20Harry%20Reid%20International%20Airport%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20Smirnov%20%26quot%3Badmitted%20that%20officials%20associated%20with%20Russian%20intelligence%20were%20involved%26quot%3B%20in%20passing%20along%20the%20story%2C%20prosecutors%20with%20special%20counsel%20David%20Weiss'%20office%20noted%20in%20a%20pretrial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24435450-governments-memorandum-in-support-of-detention-of-alexander-smirnov%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20memo%20also%20indicates%20that%20Smirnov%20met%20with%20Russian%20intelligence%20officials%20as%20recently%20as%20December%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20potential%20flight%20risk%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESmirnov%20has%20not%20responded%20directly%20to%20the%20allegations%20against%20him%2C%20though%20he%20appeared%20at%20a%20detention%20hearing%20on%20Tuesday.%20Through%20his%20lawyers%2C%20Smirnov%20has%20filed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24435485-alexander-smirnov-request-for-pretrial-release%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20motion%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20released%20pending%20trial%2C%20arguing%20he%20is%20not%20a%20flight%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20Government%20knew%20about%20Mr.%20Smirnov's%20alleged%20conduct%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20took%20no%20steps%20to%20end%20his%20cooperation%2C%20seize%20his%20passports%2C%20or%20prosecute%20him%20for%20anything%20%E2%80%94%20should%20be%20kept%20firmly%20in%20mind%20when%20(as%20expected)%20the%20Government%20reverses%20course%20in%20this%20bail%20proceeding%20and%20suddenly%20protests%20that%20Mr.%20Smirnov%20now%20presents%20an%20'extreme%20flight%20risk'%20who%20must%20be%20detained%20pending%20his%20initial%20appearance%20in%20the%20Central%20District%20of%20California%2C%26quot%3B%20Smirnov's%20lawyers%20argued%20in%20the%20motion%20to%20release%20him%20ahead%20of%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20prosecutors%20allege%20that%20Smirnov's%20%26quot%3Befforts%20to%20spread%20misinformation%20about%20a%20candidate%20of%20one%20of%20the%20two%20major%20parties%20in%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20is%20ongoing%2C%20which%20warrants%20his%20continued%20detention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Court%20should%20consider%20this%20conduct%20as%20well%20when%20evaluating%20his%20personal%20history%20and%20characteristics.%20What%20this%20shows%20is%20that%20the%20misinformation%20he%20is%20spreading%20is%20not%20confined%20to%202020%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20prosecutor's%20memo%20in%20favor%20of%20detention%20reads.%20%26quot%3BHe%20is%20actively%20peddling%20new%20lies%20that%20could%20impact%20US%20elections%20after%20meeting%20with%20Russian%20intelligence%20officials%20in%20November.%20In%20light%20of%20that%20fact%2C%20there%20is%20a%20serious%20risk%20he%20will%20flee%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20accountability%20for%20his%20actions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20ultimately%20sided%20with%20Smirnov%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F20%2Fpolitics%2Fbiden-former-fbi-informant-russian-intelligence%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%2C%20releasing%20him%20pending%20trial%20on%20the%20condition%20that%20he%20be%20subjected%20to%20GPS%20monitoring%20and%20surrender%20his%20American%20and%20Israeli%20passports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EImpact%20of%20Smirnov's%20indictment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESmirnov's%20indictment%20and%20arrest%20may%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20unrelated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunter-biden-indicted-false-statements-gun-charges-sentence-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHunter%2520Biden%2520has%2520been%2520indicted%2520on%2520charges%2520over%2520his%2520purchase%2Cwhen%2520he%2520bought%2520the%2520gun.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egun%20charges%20facing%20Hunter%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Lawyers%20for%20the%20president's%20son%20argued%20in%20a%20separate%20Tuesday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24435339%2Fhunter-biden-filing.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiling%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20special%20counsel%20David%20Weiss%20relied%20on%20Smirnov's%20allegations%20of%20bribery%20to%20blow%20up%20a%20plea%20deal%20Hunter%20Biden%20had%20agreed%20to%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeiss%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoj-alexander-smirnov-admits-russian-intelligence-behind-biden-bribery-claim2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%2