craft%20being%20used%20in%20test%20flights%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-aviation-industry-is-excited-about-flying-taxis-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edisplayed%20in%20showcases%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20worldwide.%20But%20some%20experts%20say%20if%20air%20taxis%20are%20going%20to%20go%20mainstream%2C%20an%20overlooked%20element%20will%20need%20to%20be%20scaled%20up%3A%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInfrastructure%20is%20a%20top%20priority%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20accepting%20customers%20in%20the%20US%2C%20AAM%20companies%20will%20have%20to%20go%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fair-taxis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecertification%20process%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20mandated%20by%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%2C%20which%20could%20be%20issued%20as%20early%20as%202025%20or%202026.%20From%20there%2C%20the%20process%20of%20becoming%20operational%20will%20%E2%80%9Cmove%20really%20fast%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yu%20Yu%20Zhang%2C%20the%20program%20director%20of%20advanced%20air%20mobility%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Urban%20Transportation%20Research.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%2C%20if%20specific%20infrastructure%20is%20in%20place%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20talk%20about%20infrastructure%20for%20AAM%2C%20there%20are%20two%20parts%2C%E2%80%9D%20Zhang%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20One%20part%20is%20the%20physical%20infrastructure%2C%20such%20as%20a%20vertiport%20%E2%80%94%20where%20air%20taxis%20can%20take%20off%2C%20land%2C%20and%20recharge.%20The%20other%20part%20is%20the%20digital%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20AAM%20industry%20has%20primarily%20focused%20on%20developing%20and%20certifying%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10-best-funded-electric-aviation-startups-joby-beta-evtol-startup-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20companies%20are%20beginning%20to%20build%20the%20digital%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%94%20the%20hardware%20and%20software%20that%20can%20enable%20a%20service%20%E2%80%94%20that%20will%20make%20mainstreaming%20the%20field%20possible%2C%20Zhang%20said.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20official%20process%20for%20creating%20this%20infrastructure%20yet%2C%20but%20companies%20are%20working%20toward%20an%20automated%20ecosystem%20that%20supports%20safe%20and%20efficient%20flights.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20software%20categories%20that%20fall%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-electric-air-taxi-delivered-to-us-joby-evtol-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EeVTOL%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Susan%20Shaheen%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20residence%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20and%20a%20codirector%20of%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20Transportation%20Sustainability%20Research%20Center%2C%20told%20BI.%20There%E2%80%99s%20consumer-facing%20software%20such%20as%20digital%20apps%20people%20can%20use%20to%20book%20a%20flight%20and%20back-end%20software%20for%20operations%2C%20aircraft%20control%2C%20and%20air-traffic%20management.%20The%20latter%20will%20%E2%80%9Cplay%20a%20critical%20role%20in%20ensuring%20safety%20and%20efficient%20operations%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shaheen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20digital%20solutions%20are%20in%20progress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20startups%20are%20focused%20on%20advancing%20the%20operations%20side%20of%20the%20software.%20In%20May%2C%20students%20at%20Purdue%20University%20launched%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.purdue.edu%2Fnewsroom%2Freleases%2F2023%2FQ2%2Fpurdue-startup-aerovy-mobility-develops-cloud-software-to-support-infrastructure-for-electric-aircraft.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAerovy%20Mobility%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20cloud-based%20technology%20that%20supports%20aircraft%20energy%20needs%2C%20such%20as%20recharging%20at%20a%20vertiport.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20eVTOL%20developers%20face%20specific%20software%20challenges%20related%20to%20their%20aircraft.%20For%20example%2C%20Wisk%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Boeing%2C%20developed%20an%20autonomous%20four-seat%20air%20taxi.%20Because%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20self-flying%20aircraft%2C%20there%20are%20unique%20software%20needs%2C%20Becky%20Tanner%2C%20the%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20at%20Wisk%2C%20told%20BI.%20This%20eVTOL%20uses%20software%20that%20builds%20on%20the%20same%20technology%20that%20supports%20automated%20pilot%20functions%20during%20commercial%20flights%2C%20but%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwisk.aero%2Fautonomy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eadded%20features%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20support%20pilotless%20voyages%20with%20human%20oversight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224337%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20a%20yellow%20flying%20taxi%20with%20multiple%20propellers%20around%20the%20wings.%20The%20craft%20looks%20similar%20to%20a%20large%20helicopter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb87d0f533b039a882d91d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222161%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWisk's%20Generation%206%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EWisk%20Aero%20LLC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20side%20of%20the%20software%20effort%20at%20Wisk%20is%20technology%20that%20%E2%80%9Cintegrates%20things%20from%20outside%20Wisk%20into%20Wisk%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tanner%20said.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20for%20customers%20to%20have%20%E2%80%9Cstitched-together%2C%20seamless%20experiences%20where%20they%20can%20book%20multiple%20forms%20of%20transportation%20in%20a%20one-stop%20shop%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20In%20practice%2C%20this%20could%20look%20like%20booking%20your%20Wisk%20ride%20with%20the%20same%20app%20you%20used%20to%20get%20a%20car%20to%20the%20vertiport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-pitch-deck-air-taxi-startup-volocopter-raise-170-million-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVolocopter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20German%20company%2C%20is%20approaching%20software%20holistically%20through%20a%20product%20that%20integrates%20factors%20including%20but%20not%20limited%20to%20passenger%20booking%2C%20pilot%20dispatch%2C%20airspace%20navigation%2C%20and%20battery%20management.%20The%20cloud-based%20platform%20is%20called%20VoloIQ%20and%20has%20been%20in%20development%20since%202020.%20The%20technology%20is%20supported%20by%20Microsoft%20Azure%20and%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdigital%20brains%E2%80%9D%20behind%20Volocopter%E2%80%99s%20eVTOL%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20VoloIQ%20is%20already%20live%20and%20used%20in%20test%20flights%2C%20Klaus%20Seywald%2C%20the%20director%20of%20digital%20products%20and%20strategy%20at%20Volocopter%2C%20told%20BI.%20There%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.volocopter.com%2Fen%2Fblog%2Ffrench-evolution-first-to-fly-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplans%20to%20launch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20limited%20commercial%20services%20this%20year%20in%20Paris%20and%20Rome%2C%20and%20those%20flights%20are%20set%20to%20be%20available%20to%20book%20through%20a%20VoloIQ-linked%20app.%20At%20the%20start%2C%20the%20app%20will%20show%20customers%20which%20routes%20and%20flights%20are%20available%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20Volocopter%20plans%20to%20move%20toward%20an%20on-demand%20model%2C%20Seywald%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20a%20Volocopter%20aircraft%20called%20the%20VoloCity.%20The%20craft%20is%20a%20white%20helicopter%20with%20multiple%20propellers.%20People%20are%20around%20the%20aircraft%20taking%20photos.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb899f6fcb546d2d4f0171%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222245%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVolocopter's%20air%20taxi%2C%20called%20the%20VoloCity.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Volocopter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVolocopter%20also%20sees%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstand-alone%20business%20case%E2%80%9D%20for%20VoloIQ%20as%20a%20third-party%20software%2C%20Seywald%20said.%20The%20idea%20is%20that%20rather%20than%20developing%20a%20new%20system%2C%20other%20eVTOL%20companies%20could%20use%20VoloIQ%20to%20support%20their%20products.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20problems%20it%20solves%20are%20not%20mostly%20Volocopter-specific%20but%20industry-specific%2C%E2%80%9D%20Seywald%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20air%20taxis%20in%20the%20skies%20could%20hinge%20on%20the%20customers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-software%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoftware%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20the%20success%20of%20a%20mobility%20provider%2C%20Seywald%20told%20BI.%20%E2%80%9CBuilding%20and%20certifying%20a%20new%20vehicle%20is%20one%20thing%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20think%20about%20how%20do%20you%20actually%20operate%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20certifications%20are%20within%20reach%2C%20but%20operation%2C%20I%20think%2C%20has%20not%20gotten%20enough%20attention.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeywald%20thinks%20the%20industry%20will%20start%20scaling%20around%202026%20and%20that%20by%202028%20or%202029%2C%20the%20average%20person%20will%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20and%20start%20using%20this%20mode%20of%20transportation.%20Until%20then%2C%20Shaheen%20said%2C%20AAM%20businesses%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20learn%20from%20other%20shared-mobility%20industries%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fubers-history%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20from%20shared-mobility%20deployments%20if%20you%20build%20it%2C%20riders%20do%20not%20always%20come%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20very%20important%20to%20demonstrate%20viable%20use%20cases%20and%20to%20serve%20a%20mobility%20need.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20getting%20customers%20to%20use%20flying%20taxis%20will%20hinge%20on%20addressing%20social%20barriers%20including%20safety%2C%20equity%2C%20affordability%2C%20and%20convenience%2C%20Shaheen%20said.%20In%20part%2C%20service%20providers%20can%20approach%20this%20by%20developing%20and%20using%20Americans%20with%20Disabilities%20Act-accessible%20consumer%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20software%20and%20digital%20platforms%20can%20enhance%20the%20safety%20and%20convenience%20of%20eVTOL%2C%20then%20these%20tools%20could%20help%20address%20these%20obstacles%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-connectivity-software-can-make-flying-taxis-reality-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708464441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb93ccf533b039a882e8dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-connectivity-software-can-make-flying-taxis-reality-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Flying%20taxis%20could%20even%20replace%20short-haul%20flights%2C%20but%20certification%20and%20new%20digital%20infrastructure%20must%20happen%20first.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Sloat)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-connectivity-software-can-make-flying-taxis-reality-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pak