m%2Fstory%2Famp%2Falexei-navalnys-wife-yulia-navalnaya-has-x-social-media-account-suspended-13076185%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Falexei-navalnys-wife-yulia-navalnaya-has-x-social-media-account-suspended-13076185%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Let%20me%20see%20my%20son's%20body%20-%20Navalny's%20mother%20to%20Putin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708433044000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F127C7%2Fproduction%2F_132691757_p0hczh3g.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-68349666%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lyudmila%20Navalnaya%20makes%20a%20plea%20to%20Putin%20to%20release%20Alexei's%20body%20after%20he%20died%20in%20an%20Arctic%20prison.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-68349666%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Zeherkhurani'%3A%20Nirmala%20Bhuradia's%20Latest%20Novel%20Holds%20a%20Mirror%20to%20Our%20Times%20Consumed%20by%20Hate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recently%20published%20novel%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2023)%20by%20Nirmala%20Bhuradia%20depicts%20the%20horrendous%20implications%20of%20putting%20religion%20to%20the%20worst%20abuse%20in%20the%20pursuit%20of%20remorseless%20power%20politics.%20Bhuradia%20is%20an%20Indore-based%20fiction%20writer%20and%20journalist%20and%20a%20known%20name%20in%20the%20Hindi%20literary%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20underlines%20that%20even%20decades%20after%20unprecedented%20brutalities%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20partition%2C%20humanity%20seems%20to%20have%20refused%20to%20learn%20any%20lesson.%20The%20competitive%20communal%20politics%20aggravated%20by%20the%20colonial%20state%20and%20their%20global%20power%20politics%20ruined%20the%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20decades%2C%20the%20fury%20of%20communal%20hatred%20and%20violence%20has%20resurfaced%20in%20more%20horrendous%20forms%20across%20the%20subcontinent.%20Historian%20Papiya%20Ghosh%20(1958-2006)%20aptly%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Csubcontinental%20majoritarianism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20stands%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19181050%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-6.10.21-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22328%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697834%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22305%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECover%20photo%20of%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98Zeherkhurani%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20ask%20what%20is%20so%20fresh%20about%20the%20theme%20and%20treatment%20in%20this%20novel%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhen%20there%20are%20many%20fictional%20books%20available%2C%20written%20by%20the%20tallest%20names%20in%20the%20Indian%20literary%20arena%20in%20different%20languages%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20in%20Urdu%2C%20Hindi%20and%20Punjabi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20existing%2C%20better%20known%20powerful%20stories%20(of%20Urdu%2C%20Hindi%20and%20Punjabi)%2C%20we%20hardly%20find%20the%20plight%20of%20Sindhi%20Hindu%20migrants%20who%20reside%20on%20our%20side%20of%20the%20border.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20the%20contemporary%20resurgence%20of%20hatred%2C%20violence%20and%20identity-politics%2C%20exacerbated%20much%20by%20the%20media%20and%20all%20pervasive%20social%20media%20is%20a%20novelty%20about%20the%20novel%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20theme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20treatment%20of%20the%20theme%20is%20dexterous.%20The%20story%20has%20been%20weaved%20brilliantly.%20The%20pains%20inflicted%20upon%20the%20many%20tragic%20characters%2C%20mostly%20women%20and%20some%20men%2C%20are%20something%20that%20the%20readers%20are%20bound%20to%20feel%20so%20very%20deeply%20and%20strongly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fin-a-world-of-borders-ones-search-for-a-home-can-tell-a-story%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20World%20of%20Borders%2C%20One%E2%80%99s%20Search%20for%20a%20Home%20Can%20Tell%20a%20Story%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Sindh%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20notable%20historical%20studies%20on%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20Sindh%20is%20concerned%20as%20a%20provincial%20territory%20which%20remained%20wholly%20with%20Pakistan%20unlike%20Punjab%20and%20Bengal.%20The%20Hindus%20of%20Sindh%20had%20to%20suffer%20either%20from%20the%20subjugation%20of%20the%20Muslim%20majoritarianism%20or%20had%20to%20migrate%20to%20parts%20which%20were%20to%20fall%20in%20India%20after%20August%2014-15%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Cem%3Egarm%20hawa%3C%2Fem%3E%20(hot%20air)%20of%20hatred%2C%20violence%2C%20rape%20and%20plunder%20blew%2C%20they%20were%20uprooted.%20Their%20journey%20from%20Karachi%20to%20Bombay%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20India%2C%20including%20Central%20India%20(Madhya%20Pradesh)%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20quite%20horrific.%20They%20were%20hardly%20familiar%20with%20places%20beyond%20their%20birthplace%20Sindh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20settlement%20within%20India%20made%20them%20realise%20that%20even%20among%20their%20own%20co-religionists%20they%20were%20mocked%2C%20marginalised%2C%20discriminated%2C%20and%20they%20were%20looked%20upon%20with%20contempt%20for%20their%20distinct%20language%2Fdialect%2C%20accents%2C%20culture%2C%20appearances%2C%20sartorial%20styles%2C%20etc.%20Their%20children%20studying%20in%20schools%20had%20to%20suffer%20from%20various%20kinds%20of%20segregation%20and%20ostracisation.%20Yet%2C%20they%20rebuilt%20their%20lives%20in%20trade%20and%20education%2C%20with%20their%20hard%20work%20and%20with%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESarah%20F.D.%20Ansari%E2%80%99s%20books%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20historical%20study%20on%20Sindh%20is%20highlighted%20by%20Sarah%20F.D.%20Ansari%20in%20her%20works.%20She%20wrote%20two%20books%20consecutively%20on%20late%20colonial%20and%20then%20on%20post-colonial%20period.%20These%20are%2C%20however%2C%20mostly%20on%20the%20Muslims%20who%20were%20(and%20are)%20anyway%20majority%20in%20the%20province.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnsari%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3ESufi%20Saints%20and%20State%20Power%3A%20The%20Pirs%20of%20Sind%2C%201843%E2%80%931947%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1992)%20examines%20the%20system%20of%20political%20control%20constructed%20by%20the%20British%20in%20Sind%20between%201843%20and%201947.%20She%20throws%20light%20on%20the%20local%20Muslim%20religious%20elite%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Epirs%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20hereditary%20%3Cem%3Esufi%3C%2Fem%3E%20saints%2C%20whose%20participation%20in%20the%20system%20ensured%20the%20politics%20of%20vivisecting%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20in%20particular.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3ELife%20After%20Partition%3A%20Migration%2C%20Community%20and%20Strife%20in%20Sindh%201947%20%E2%80%931962%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2005)%2C%20she%20examines%20the%20historical%20background%20%E2%80%93%20studying%20the%20years%20following%20partition%20%E2%80%93%20as%20ethnic%20politics%20had%20come%20to%20dominate%20Sindh%20by%20the%201990s%20with%20calls%20for%20Karachi%20to%20become%20a%20fifth%20province%20in%20its%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20stands%20out%20since%20it%20attempts%20to%20fill%20specific%20gaps%20of%20fictional%20articulation%20while%20historical%20exploration%20of%20the%20plight%20of%20the%20Sindhi%20Hindus%20among%20the%20Hindu%20majority%20of%20India%20is%20perhaps%20still%20awaited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20story%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20protagonist%20of%20the%20story%20is%20an%20inquisitive%20and%20interrogative%20girl%20Minali%20alias%20Minni%2C%20born%20in%201960%2C%20who%20grows%20up%20as%20a%20fiercely%20rational%20and%20a%20believer%20in%20pluralist%20coexistence.%20She%20chooses%20journalism%20as%20a%20profession%20which%20gets%20depressingly%20sallied%20by%20the%20time%20Minni%20and%20her%20husband%20reach%20their%2050s.%20Theirs%20is%20an%20almost%20lonely%20battle%20against%20the%20highly%20polarised%20society.%20The%20polarisation%20is%20because%20of%20many%20stereotypes%20against%20religious%20communities%2C%20fed%20mostly%20by%20communalised%20media%20owned%20by%20greedy%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinni%E2%80%99s%20cousin%2C%20Manohar%2C%20a%20hoodlum%2C%20lumpen%2C%20and%20eve-teaser%20grows%20up%20to%20become%20an%20important%20cadre%20of%20a%20communalised%20political%20party%20which%20eventually%20gets%20elected%20to%20power%2C%20riding%20on%20the%20wave%20of%20communal%20polarisation%2C%20hatred%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManufacturing%20rumours%2C%20history%2C%20falsehood%20and%20concoctions%20are%20something%20his%20politics%20thrives%20on.%20Remarkably%2C%20Nirmala%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20the%20causation%20of%20partition%20is%20very%20good.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20novels%20in%20which%20the%20British%20culpability%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20partition%20has%20been%20brought%20out%20most%20clearly.%20For%20instance%2C%20when%20the%20British%20Governor%20of%20Punjab%20E.%20M.%20Jenkins%20(1896-1985)%20was%20frustrated%20by%20Khizr%20Hayat%20Khan%20Tiwana%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20to%20the%20partition%2C%20Tiwana%E2%80%99s%20government%20was%20toppled%20and%20the%20League%E2%80%99s%20was%20installed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%20aspects%20highlighted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20shy%20away%20from%20highlighting%20the%20radicalisation%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20the%201970s%20and%201980s%2C%20internecine%20sectarian%20violence%20and%20absolute%20derailment%20of%20the%20economic%20progress%2C%20social%20fabric%20in%20tatters%2C%20as%20much%20as%20India%20is%20also%20increasingly%20becoming%20its%20mirror-image%2C%20transforming%20its%20republic%20into%20a%20theocracy.%20The%20fictional%20depiction%20acts%20as%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fmodern-asian-studies%2Fissue%2F2E7479A370611ADC31E07FB07A01DBD3%5C%22%3Eessay%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20V.S.%20Kalra%20and%20Waqas%20Butt%2C%20%E2%80%98If%20I%20Speak%2C%20They%20Will%20Kill%20Me%2C%20to%20Remain%20Silent%20Is%20to%20Die%E2%80%99%3A%20Poetry%20of%20resistance%20in%20General%20Zia%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%20(1977%E2%80%9388)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fmodern-asian-studies%2Fissue%2F2E7479A370611ADC31E07FB07A01DBD3%5C%22%3E(2019)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20during%20the%20very%20same%20decades%2C%20India%20too%20has%20been%20witnessing%20a%20consistent%20rise%20and%20expansion%20of%20identitarian%20forces.%20It%20resurged%20in%20the%20name%20of%20crusading%20against%20authoritarianism%20called%20Emergency.%20Some%20of%20these%20forces%20of%20resistance%20preferred%20to%20call%20themselves%20%E2%80%9CSmugglers%20of%20Truth%E2%80%9D%2C%20who%20found%20lots%20of%20support%20and%20funds%20from%20the%20expatriates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20the%20regressivism%20and%20bigotry%20of%20the%20affluent%20Non-Resident%20Indians%20(NRIs)%2C%20the%20scholar-journalist%20Arvind%20N%20Das%20(1949-2000)%20had%20once%20written%20a%20column%2C%20%E2%80%9CLong%20Distance%20Nationalism%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3EFrontline%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20November%204%2C%201994).%20The%20expression%20is%20borrowed%20from%20Benedict%20Anderson%E2%80%99s%201983%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EImagined%20Communities%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20roles%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CSmugglers%20of%20Truth%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20exposed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fmodern-asian-studies%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fsmugglers-of-truth-the-indian-diaspora-hindu-nationalism-and-the-emergency-197577%2F2C59B29D6C36D0CA7C8B1C2EE207534D%5C%22%3Erecent%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2018).%20The%20rapid%20communalisation%20culminated%20into%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20of%201984%20and%20ever%20since%20then%2C%20bigotry%2C%20hatred%2C%20strife%20and%20pogroms%20kept%20becoming%20more%20a%20socio-political%20mainstream%20than%20a%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20possibly%20attempts%20to%20pin%20hope%20of%20a%20good%20future%20on%20the%20rationalist-pluralist%20women%20(and%20men)%20intelligentsia%20and%20journalists.%20This%20optimism%2C%20though%20not%20misplaced%2C%20needs%20some%20quantum%20of%20reservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20educated%20middle%20classes%20and%20the%20affluent%20ones%20are%20not%20necessarily%20committed%20to%20humanitarianism%20and%20justice.%20Greed%20for%20name%2C%20fame%2C%20pelf%20and%20power%20of%20these%20classes%20across%20the%20globe%20has%20pushed%20the%20world%20into%20the%20vortex%20of%20bigotry%2C%20fanaticism%2C%20hatred%20and%20violence.%20This%20has%20aggravated%20in%20recent%20decades%20even%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Byung-Chul%20Han%E2%80%99s%20recent%20book(let)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Ffan-publication%2Fanti-networks-and-a-review-of-byung-chan-hans-psychopolitics-6c2ada673bb2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPsychopolitics%2520is%2520a%2520fascinating%2520and%2Cproductive%252C%2520useful%2520strategy%2520or%2520platforms.%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPsychopolitics%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20fascinating%20and%20well-written%20treatise%20on%20subjects%20that%20feel%20beaten%20to%20death%2C%20and%20is%20situated%20within%20a%20radical%20culture%20seemingly%20damned%20to%20futility%20by%20capitalist%20realism%20and%20one%20incapable%20of%20generating%20productive%2C%20useful%20strategy%20or%20platforms%E2%80%9D%20of%20resistance%20and%20solidarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiction%20writers%20may%20derive%20creative%20insights%20from%20such%20works%20capturing%20the%20harsh%20realities%20of%20our%20times.%20Bhuradia%20is%20one%20such%20fiction%20writer%20of%20our%20times%20who%20is%20engaged%20in%20the%20pursuit%20of%20fictional%20articulation%20of%20the%20contemporary%20horrors%20of%20humans%20against%20fellow%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20critical%20observations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20seven%20chapters%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20depicting%20the%20recent%20decades%2C%20have%20become%20a%20little%20less%20creative%20in%20terms%20of%20artistic%20finesse.%20Nonetheless%2C%20the%20novel%20does%20hold%20a%20mirror%20before%20all%20of%20us%20about%20the%20way%20we%20are%2C%20as%20of%20now%2C%20and%20what%20we%20are%20likely%20to%20become%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%20towards%20rescuing%20the%20pluralist%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20seems%20to%20be%20concerned%20with%20depicting%20only%20the%20minorities%2C%20including%20the%20minorities%20within%20the%20minorities.%20Thus%2C%20Sindhi%20Hindu%20families%20on%20the%20margins%20of%20Hindu%20majority%20society%2C%20Bohras%20among%20the%20Muslims%2C%20with%20their%20own%20regressive%20cultural%20practices%20and%20subjugation%20of%20women%2C%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20a%20particular%20version%20of%20religion%2C%20and%20the%20Sikhs%20find%20their%20stories%20of%20suffering%20in%20this%20novel.%20Dalits%20left%20in%20Pakistan%20too%20have%20found%20a%20mention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eventual%20disintegration%20of%20the%20once%20vivacious%20Mangal%20Bhawan%20and%20the%20Fatima%20Manzil%2C%20find%20a%20brilliant%20creative%20articulation.%20Intra-community%20oppressions%20(and%20horrific%20patriarchy%20perpetuating%20with%20growing%20superstitions)%20against%20the%20rationalists%20and%20pluralists%20are%20the%20running%20themes%20in%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state-%20(and%20religion-)%20driven%20feeding%20of%20communal%20poison%20is%20a%20running%20theme%20throughout%20the%20story%20and%20stories%20within%20the%20story%20of%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-nilanjana-sengupta-chickpeas-singapore%5C%22%3EThe%20Gods%20in%20Our%20Kitchens%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20emotional%20aspect%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20highlights%20how%20polarisation%2C%20madness%2C%20violence%20and%20tremendous%20brutalities%20make%20victims%20mentally%20sick.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20character%20of%20the%20child%20Banta%20is%20written%20in%20such%20a%20manner%20that%20it%20will%20make%20readers%20cry%20on%20multiple%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanta%2C%20separated%20from%20his%20parents%2C%20is%20subjected%20to%20mutilations%20and%20torture%20several%20times.%20Each%20time%20the%20boy%20is%20made%20to%20change%20his%20religious%20identity%2C%20he%20is%20face%20to%20face%20with%20the%20rioters%20of%20the%20rival%20identity.%20Even%20his%20part%20pretension%20and%20part%20reality%20of%20having%20become%20dumb%2C%20or%20resorting%20to%20become%20luminal%20in%20identitarian%20terms%20(such%20as%20chanting%20Bulley%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20poetry%3A%20%3Cem%3EBulleyh%20Kih%20Jaana%20Main%20Kaun%3C%2Fem%3E)%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20ensure%20his%20safety%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20violent%20religious%20orthodoxy%20of%20various%20hues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20despite%20having%20been%20circumcised%2C%20his%20Sikh%20identity%20gets%20revealed%20and%20he%20ends%20up%20losing%20even%20the%20circumcised%20organ%20altogether.%20With%20this%20horrific%20loss%2C%20he%20does%20get%20re-united%20with%20his%20father%2C%20who%20has%20already%20abandoned%20his%20mother%2C%20as%20she%20was%20abducted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMental%20illness%20has%20been%20inflicted%20upon%20such%20victims%20by%20the%20society.%20With%20such%20characters%20in%20the%20story%2C%20one%20is%20reminded%20of%20Michel%20Focault%E2%80%99s%201961%20edition%20of%20the%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EMadness%20and%20Civilization%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20wherein%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CModern%20man%20no%20longer%20communicates%20with%20the%20madman%20%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20no%20common%20language%2C%20or%20rather%2C%20it%20no%20longer%20exists%3B%20the%20constitution%20of%20madness%20as%20mental%20illness%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20bears%20witness%20to%20a%20rupture%20in%20a%20dialogue%2C%20gives%20the%20separation%20as%20already%20enacted%2C%20and%20expels%20from%20the%20memory%20all%20those%20imperfect%20words%2C%20of%20no%20fixed%20syntax%2C%20spoken%20falteringly%2C%20in%20which%20the%20exchange%2C%20between%20madness%20and%20reason%2C%20was%20carried%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20novel%20is%20not%20only%20about%20the%20darker%20aspects.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20fail%20to%20capture%20the%20anecdotes%20of%20people%20rising%20against%20the%20violence%20and%20hatred%20and%20helping%20their%20neighbourhood%20defying%20the%20politically%20foisted%20religious%20divides%20and%20polarisation.%20Such%20characters%20and%20anecdotes%20give%20a%20little%20respite%20from%20the%20horrific%20sufferings%20of%20the%20humans%20that%20runs%20through%20the%20story%20and%20it%20also%20offers%20hope%20that%20such%20dark%20phases%20shall%20pass%20away%20sooner%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20novel%20is%20a%20diagnosis%20of%20and%20a%20very%20damning%20charge-sheet%20against%20the%20crime%20of%20hatred%20and%20violence%20being%20committed%20by%20humans%20against%20humans%20in%20our%20times.%20It%E2%80%99s%20definitely%20a%20must-read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fmohammad-sajjad%5C%22%3EMohammad%20Sajjad%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20History%20at%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0Muslim%20Politics%20in%20Bihar%3A%20Changing%20Contours.%20He%20tweets%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsajjadhist%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3E%40sajjadhist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708432195000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fzeherkhurani-nirmala-bhuradias-latest-novel-holds-mirror-to-our-times-consumed-by-hate%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20Hindi%20novel%20underlines%20that%20even%20decades%20after%20unprecedented%20brutalities%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20partition%2C%20humanity%20seems%20to%20have%20refused%20to%20learn%20any%20lesson.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fzeherkhurani-nirmala-bhuradias-latest-novel-holds-mirror-to-our-times-consumed-by-hate%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20frustration%20with%20Israel%20has%20grown%20in%20recent%20weeks%20-%20and%20new%20UN%20resolution%20is%20sign%20of%20that%20displeasure%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708431900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-navalny-alexei-joe_6458241.jpg%3F20240216201557%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-us-frustration-has-grown-in-recent-weeks-and-new-un-resolution-is-sign-of-that-displeasure-13076165%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Washington's%20unwavering%20diplomatic%20support%20for%20Israel%20at%20the%20UN%20has%20put%20the%20US%20in%20an%20increasingly%20isolated%20position%20as%20many%20of%20the%20world's%20countries%20have%20called%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20fighting%20in%20Gaza.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A298%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-us-frustration-has-grown-in-recent-weeks-and-new-un-resolution-is-sign-of-that-displeasure-13076165%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-us-frustration-has-grown-in-recent-weeks-and-new-un-resolution-is-sign-of-that-displeasure-13076165%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-us-frustration-has-grown-in-recent-weeks-and-new-un-resolution-is-sign-of-that-displeasure-13076165%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2221%20Starbucks%20Stores%20Plan%20To%20Form%20Unions%20In%201-Day%20Blitz%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20union%20Workers%20United%20has%20organized%20roughly%20400%20stores%2C%20but%20is%20locked%20in%20a%20bitter%20bargaining%20fight%20with%20the%20coffee%20chain.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708430583000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fimg.huffingtonpost.com%2Fasset%2F65c26b16230000124c80809c.jpeg%3Fcache%3DOd4V54hk31%26ops%3D1200_630%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20union%20Workers%20United%20has%20organized%20roughly%20400%20stores%2C%20but%20is%20locked%20in%20a%20bitter%20bargaining%20fight%20with%20the%20coffee%20chain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A287%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-huffpost-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%2Famp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%2Famp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Of%20Magic%20Beans%20and%20Modified%20Mustard%3A%20How%20GMOs%20Will%20Destroy%20Indian%20Agriculture%20and%20Impact%20Health%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20154101%2Fdietmar-kraus-qtgR-PgjVV4-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20Bt%20cotton%2C%20the%20only%20commercialised%20Genetically%20Modified%20crop%20in%20India%2C%20has%20failed%20conclusively.%20Based%20on%20this%20failure%20and%20the%20evidence%20of%20the%20clear%20harm%20that%20GM%20Organisms%20(GMOs)%20will%20cause%20to%20human%20and%20animal%20health%2C%20the%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20to%20commercialise%20herbicide-tolerant%20(HT)%20mustard%20will%20destroy%20not%20just%20Indian%20mustard%20agriculture%2C%20but%20citizens%E2%80%99%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJanuary%20witnessed%20five%20days%20of%20intense%20hearings%20on%20this%20matter%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC)%20%E2%80%94%20the%20GMO%20Public%20Interest%20Writ%20filed%20almost%2020%20years%20ago%20in%202005%20by%20the%20author%2C%20which%20ended%20on%20January%2018%2C%202024.%20In%20these%20last%2020%20years%2C%20piecemeal%20hearings%20have%20dealt%20with%20submissions%20relating%20to%20individual%20crops%20like%20hybrid%20Bt%20cotton%2C%20the%20attempted%20commercialisation%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20brinjal%20(2010)%20and%20now%20the%20attempt%20to%20commercialise%20hybrid%20HT%20mustard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20provided%20here%20is%20a%20distillation%20of%20the%20critical%20inputs%20of%20those%2060%2B%20submissions%20based%20on%20the%20affidavits%20and%20studies%20of%20leading%2C%20independent%20scientists%20and%20experts%20of%20international%20renown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20a%20serious%20and%20proven%20conflict%20of%20interest%20among%20our%20regulators%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20along%20with%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR)%2C%20which%20promote%20GMOs%20in%20Indian%20agriculture.%20This%20evidence%20reflects%20in%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20TEC%20Report%20(Technical%20Expert%20Committee)%20appointed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC)%20in%202012%20and%20two%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committees%20of%202012%20and%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Modern%20biotechnology%E2%80%99%20or%20genetically%20modified%20organisms%20(GMOs)%20are%20products%20where%20the%20genomes%20of%20organisms%20are%20transformed%20through%20laboratory%20techniques%2C%20including%20genetically%20engineered%20DNA%20(recombinant)%20and%20its%20direct%20introduction%20into%20cells.%20These%20are%20techniques%20not%20used%20in%20traditional%20breeding%20and%20selection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGMOs%20create%20organisms%20in%20ways%20that%20have%20never%20existed%20in%203.8%20billion%20years%20of%20evolution%20and%20produce%20%E2%80%98unintended%20effects%E2%80%99%20that%20are%20not%20immediately%20apparent.%20This%20is%20why%20rigorous%2C%20independent%20protocols%20for%20risk%20and%20hazard%20identification%20are%20the%20sine%20qua%20non%20of%20correct%20regulation%20in%20the%20public%20interest.%20The%20Indian%20%E2%80%98Rules%20of%201989%E2%80%99%20%5BRules%20for%20the%20Manufacture%2FUse%2FImport%2FExport%20and%20Storage%20of%20Hazardous%20Microorganisms%2F%20Genetically%20Engineered%20Organisms%20or%20Cells%2C%201989%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20Environment%20(Protection)%20Act%2C%201986%5D%20describe%20GMOs%20as%20%E2%80%9Chazardous%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20outstanding%20concern%20is%20contamination%20of%20the%20natural%20environment%20(including%20the%20cross-transfer%20of%20pollen%20by%20bees%20to%20wild%20or%20other%20domestic%20crop%20varieties)%20by%20GMOs%3B%20a%20worry%20that%20the%20Convention%20on%20Biological%20Diversity%20%E2%80%93%20which%20India%20is%20a%20signatory%20to%20%E2%80%93%20also%20recognises.%20India%20is%20one%20of%2017%20listed%20international%20hotspots%20of%20diversity%2C%20which%20includes%20mustard%2C%20brinjal%20and%20rice.%20India%20is%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biological%20diversity%20in%20brinjal%2C%20with%20over%202%2C500%20varieties%20grown%20in%20the%20country%20and%20as%20many%20as%2029%20wild%20species.%20India%20is%20also%20a%20secondary%20centre%20of%20origin%20of%20rape-seed%20mustard%20with%20over%209%2C000%20accessions%20in%20our%20gene%20bank%20(National%20Bureau%20of%20Plant%20Genetic%20Resources).%20With%20a%20commercialised%20GM%20crop%2C%20contamination%20is%20certain.%20The%20precautionary%20principle%20must%20apply%2C%20is%20read%20into%20the%20Constitution%20and%20is%20a%20legal%20precedent%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20was%20introduced%20in%202002%20and%20remains%20the%20only%20approved%20commercialised%20crop%20in%20India.%20It%20has%20been%20an%20abject%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFailure%20of%20Bt%20cotton%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20the%20only%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20have%20introduced%20the%20Bt%20gene%20into%20hybrid%20Bt%20Cotton.%C2%A0%20It%20was%20introduced%20in%20hybrids%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98value-capture%20mechanism%E2%80%99%2C%20according%20to%20K.R.%20Kranthi%2C%20a%20professor%20with%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20of%20research%20in%20cotton%20who%20was%20also%20the%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Central%20Institute%20for%20Cotton%20Research%20(CICR).%20The%20hybrid%20technology%20disallows%20seed%20saving%20by%20millions%20of%20small%20farmers.%20Conservative%20estimates%20indicate%20that%20Indian%20farmers%20may%20have%20paid%20an%20additional%20amount%20of%20Rs%2014%2C000%20crore%20for%20Bt%20cotton%20seeds%20between%202002%20and%202018%2C%20of%20which%20trait%20fees%20(an%20amount%20paid%20to%20developers%20of%20the%20seeds%20for%20using%20their%20technology)%20alone%20amounted%20to%20Rs%207%2C337.37%20crore%2C%20said%20Kranthi.%20There%20was%20also%20a%20phenomenal%20three-fold%20increase%20in%20labour%20costs%20in%20hybrid%20cotton%20cultivation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Gutierrez%2C%20Professor%20Emeritus%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20Science%2C%20Policy%20and%20Management%20in%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20is%20among%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20leading%20entomologists%20and%20cotton%20scientists.%20He%20provided%20the%20ecological%20explanation%20of%20why%20hybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20is%20every%20bit%20a%20disaster%20that%20it%20is%20in%20India.%20Most%20hybrid%20cottons%20are%20long%20season%20(180-200-day%20duration).%20This%20increases%20the%20opportunities%20for%20pest%20resurgence%20and%20outbreaks%20because%20it%20links%20into%20the%20lifecycle%20of%20the%20pest.%20The%20low-density%20planting%20also%20increases%20the%20cost%20of%20hybrid%20seeds%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrids%20require%20stable%20water%20too%20(therefore%2C%20irrigation%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20rain-fed)%20and%20more%20fertiliser.%20Some%2090%25%20of%20current%20Bt%20cotton%20hybrids%20appear%20susceptible%20to%20sap-sucking%20insects%2C%20leaf-curl%20virus%20and%20leaf%20reddening%2C%20adding%20to%20input%20costs%20and%20loss%20of%20yield.%20Most%20telling%20is%20that%20India%20produces%20only%203.3%20million%20tonnes%20from%20its%20irrigated%20area%20of%204.9%20million%20hectares%20compared%20to%206.96%20million%20tonnes%20from%20an%20equivalent%20area%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20in%20India%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20yield%20plateau%2C%20high%20production%20costs%20and%20low%20productivity%20that%20reduce%20farmer%20revenues%2C%20correlated%20with%20increased%20farmer%20distress%20and%20suicides.%20It%20has%20stymied%20the%20development%20of%20economically%20viable%20high-density%20short-season%20(HD-SS)%20Non-Bt%20high-yielding%20straight-line%20varieties.%20The%20failure%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20is%20an%20abject%20lesson%20for%20GMO%20implementation%20in%20other%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20regulators%20attempted%20to%20repeat%20history%20in%20the%20form%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20brinjal%20and%20hybrid%20HT%20mustard.%20This%2C%20despite%20field%20trial%20solutions%20(CICR%20data)%20of%20high-density%20short-season%20(HD-SS)%20NON-GMO%20pure-line%20(non-hybrid)%2C%20rainfed%20cotton%20varieties%20being%20developed%20in%20India%20that%20could%20more%20than%20double%20yield%20and%20nearly%20triple%20net%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20admitted%20in%20its%20affidavit%20in%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20(January%2022%2C%202016)%2C%20adding%2C%20(on%20January%2023%2C%202017)%2C%20that%20Bt%20%E2%80%9Ccotton%20seeds%20are%20now%20unaffordable%20to%20farmers%20due%20to%20high%20royalties%20charged%20by%20MMBL%20(Mahyco%20Monsanto%20Biotech%20Ltd)%20which%20has%20a%20near%20monopoly%20on%20Bt%20cotton%20seeds%20and%20that%20this%20has%20led%20to%20a%20market%20failure%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20there%20is%20no%20trait%20for%20yield%20enhancement%20in%20the%20Bt%20technology.%20Any%20intrinsic%20yield%20increase%20is%20properly%20attributable%20to%20its%20hybridisation%20in%20both%20Bt%20cotton%20and%20Bt%20brinjal.%20Lower%20insecticide%20use%20is%20the%20reason%20for%20introducing%20the%20Bt%20technology%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pink%20bollworm%20has%20developed%20high%20levels%20of%20resistance%20against%20Bollgard-II%20Bt%20cotton%2C%20leading%20to%20increased%20insecticide%20usage%20in%20India%2C%20increases%20in%20new%20induced%20secondary%20pests%20and%20crop%20failures.%20The%20annual%20report%202015-16%20of%20the%20ICAT-CICR%20confirms%20that%20Bt%20cotton%20is%20no%20longer%20effective%20for%20bollworm%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInsecticide%20usage%20on%20cotton%20in%202002%20was%200.88%20kg%20per%20hectare%2C%20which%20increased%20to%200.97%20kg%20per%20hectare%20in%202013%20(Srivastav%20and%20Kolady%202016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatters%20were%20deliberately%20muddied%20in%20India%2C%20leading%20to%20any%20hybrid%20vigour%20being%20attributed%20to%20the%20Bt%20technology!%20Yields%20have%20stagnated%20despite%20the%20deployment%20of%20all%20available%20latest%20technologies%2C%20including%20the%20introduction%20of%20new%20potent%20GM%20technologies%2C%20a%20two-fold%20increase%20in%20the%20use%20of%20fertilisers%20and%20increased%20insecticide%20use%20and%20irrigation.%20And%20yet%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20rank%20is%2030-32nd%20in%20terms%20of%20yield.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%2013%20years%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20increased%20302%25.%20In%2015%20years%2C%20there%20was%20a%20450%25%20increase%20in%20labour%20costs.%20The%20costs%20of%20hybrid%20seed%2C%20insecticide%20and%20fertiliser%20increased%20more%20than%20250%20to%20300%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20profit%20for%20farmers%20was%20Rs.%205971%2Fha%20in%202003%20(pre-Bt)%20but%20plummeted%20to%20net%20losses%20of%20Rs%206%2C286%20in%202015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feands.dacnet.nic.in%2FCost_of_Cultivation.htm%2520Cost%2520of%2520cultivation%2520%2F%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20Kranthi%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegulatory%20failure%3A%20Bt%20brinjal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegulators%20tried%20to%20commercialise%20Bt%20brinjal%20and%20its%20hybrids%20in%202009.%20The%20Bt%20gene%20is%20proven%20to%20be%20undeniably%20toxic%20(experts%20including%20David%20Schubert%2C%20former%20professor%20and%20head%20of%20the%20Cellular%20Neurobiology%20Laboratory%20at%20the%20Salk%20Institute%20for%20Biological%20Studies%20in%20La%20Jolla%2C%20CA%3B%20Arpad%20Pusztai%2C%20former%20professor%20at%20the%20Rowett%20Research%20Institute%20in%20Aberdeen%3B%20Gilles-%C3%89ric%20S%C3%A9ralini%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20molecular%20biology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Caen%2C%20France%20and%20others%20have%20confirmed%20this).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202008%2C%20the%20regulators%20were%20forced%20to%20publish%20the%20developers%E2%80%99%20(Monsanto-Mahyco)%20self-assessed%20bio-safety%20dossier%20on%20their%20website%2C%2016%20months%20after%20the%20order%20of%20the%20SC%20to%20make%20the%20safety%20dossier%20data%20public%20(February%2015%2C%202007).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBt%20brinjal%20was%20the%20first%20vegetable%20food%20crop%20in%20the%20world%20to%20be%20approved%20for%20commercialisation%2C%20by%20the%20collective%20regulatory%20body%20and%20their%20expert%20committees%2C%20virtually%20without%20oversight.%20When%20the%20international%20scientific%20community%20examined%20the%20raw%20data%2C%20their%20collective%20comments%20were%20scathing.%20Jack%20Heinemann%2C%20Professor%20of%20Molecular%20Biology%20and%20Genetics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Canterbury%20stated%20that%20Mahyco%20has%20failed%20at%20the%20first%2C%20elementary%20step%20of%20the%20safety%20study%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20never%20seen%20less%20professionalism%20in%20the%20presentation%20and%20quality%20assurance%20of%20molecular%20data%20than%20in%20this%20study%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20criticised%20Mahyco%20for%20using%20outdated%20studies%2C%20testing%20to%20below%20acceptable%20standards%20and%20using%20inappropriate%20and%20invalid%20test%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20comprehensive%20critique%20of%20Monsanto%E2%80%99s%20Dossier%20%E2%80%98Bt%20brinjal%20Event%20EE1%E2%80%99%2C%20David%20Andow%20%E2%80%93%20a%20Distinguished%20McKnight%20University%20Professor%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Entomology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20%E2%80%93%20listed%2037%20studies%20of%20which%20perhaps%20one%20had%20been%20conducted%20and%20reported%20to%20a%20satisfactory%20level%20by%20Monsanto.%20He%20concluded%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20GEAC%20set%20too%20narrow%20a%20scope%20for%20environmental%20risk%20assessment%20(ERA)%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20brinjal%2C%20and%20it%20is%20because%20of%20this%20overly%20narrow%20scope%20that%20the%20EC-II%20is%20not%20an%20adequate%20ERA%E2%80%A6%20most%20of%20the%20possible%20environmental%20risks%20of%20Bt%20brinjal%20have%20not%20been%20adequately%20evaluated%3B%20this%20includes%20risks%20to%20local%20varieties%20of%20brinjal%20and%20wild%20relatives%2C%20risks%20to%20biological%20diversity%2C%20and%20risk%20of%20resistance%20evolution%20in%20BFSB.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Central%20government%20itself%20declared%20an%20unconditional%20and%20indefinite%20moratorium%20on%20Bt%20brinjal%20in%20February%202009%20based%20on%20the%20collective%20responses%20of%20the%20scientific%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisaster%20in%20the%20making%3A%20GM%20Hybrid%20HT%20Mustard%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20Bt%2C%20HT%20is%20a%20pesticidal%20crop%20(to%20kill%20weeds).%20These%20two%20GMO%20technologies%20represent%20about%2098%25%20of%20crops%20planted%20worldwide%2C%20with%20HT%20crops%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%2080%25.%20Neither%20has%20a%20trait%20for%20yield.%20In%20its%202002%20Report%2C%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20for%20Agriculture%20stated%3A%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Ccurrently%20available%20GM%20crops%20do%20not%20increase%20the%20yield%20potential%E2%80%A6%20In%20fact%2C%20yield%20may%20even%20decrease%20if%20the%20%3Cu%3Evarieties%20%3C%2Fu%3Eused%20to%20carry%20the%20herbicide%20tolerant%20or%20insect-resistant%20genes%20are%20not%20the%20highest%20yielding%20cultivars%E2%80%A6%20Perhaps%20the%20biggest%20issue%20raised%20by%20these%20results%20is%20how%20to%20explain%20the%20rapid%20adoption%20of%20GE%20crops%20when%20farm%20financial%20impacts%20appear%20to%20be%20mixed%20or%20even%20negative.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20developer%E2%80%99s%20(Centre%20for%20Genetic%20Manipulation%20of%20Crop%20Plants%20University%20of%20Delhi)%20bio-safety%20dossier%2C%20in%20contempt%20of%20the%20SC%20orders%2C%20has%20never%20made%20its%20data%20public.%20A%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20request%20was%20filed%20in%202016%20with%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Rape-Seed%20Mustard%20Research%2C%20which%20conducts%20protocols%20of%20non-GMO%20mustard%20trials%20for%20crop%20improvement%20programmes%20for%20our%20farmers%2C%20for%20varietal%20stability%20and%20performance.%20The%20RTI%20was%20an%20eye%20opener.%20Virtually%20all%20the%20directorate%E2%80%99s%20norms%20were%20flouted%20in%20the%20field%20trials%2C%20making%20them%20invalid.%20Hybrid%20mustard%20HT%20DMH%2011%20was%20out-yielded%20by%20more%20than%20the%2010%25%20norm%20by%20non-GMO%20varieties%20and%20hybrids%2C%20which%20forced%20the%20developers%20to%20admit%20this%20fact%20in%20their%20formal%20reply%20affidavit%20in%20the%20SC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrid%20HT%20mustard%20DMH%2011%20employs%20three%20transgenes%3A%20the%20male%20sterility%20gene%2C%20barnase%2C%20the%20female%20restorer%20gene%2C%20barstar%2C%20and%20the%20bar%20gene%20that%20confers%20tolerance%20to%20Bayer%E2%80%99s%20herbicide%20glufosinate%20ammonium%20or%20basta.%20Each%20of%20the%20parent%20lines%20has%20the%20bar%20gene%20that%20makes%20them%20both%20HT%20crops%20along%20with%20their%20resulting%20hybrid%20DMH%2011.%20The%20reason%20for%20employing%20barnase%20and%20barstar%20is%20because%20mustard%20is%20a%20closed%20pollinating%20crop%20(even%20though%20it%20out%20crosses%20pretty%20well%2C%2018%25%2B)%20and%20this%20technology%20(a%20male%20sterility%20technology)%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20produce%20mustard%20hybrids.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20hybrid%20technology.%20Its%20counterpart%20in%20non-GMO%20male%20sterility%20technology%20is%20the%20CMS%20system%20(cytoplasmic%20male%20sterility).%20Employing%20male%20sterility%20in%20mustard%20allows%20it%20to%20be%20used%20more%20easily%20in%20already%20existing%20hybridisation%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20curious%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20the%20regulators%20have%20tried%20to%20obfuscate%20the%20facts%20and%20muddy%20the%20waters.%20Their%20first%20response%20was%20that%20the%20acronym%20HT%20in%20mustard%20DMH%2011%20means%20%E2%80%98hybrid%20technology%E2%80%99.%20When%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20the%20next%20%E2%80%98try%E2%80%99%20was%20that%20DMH%2011%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20HT%20crop!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20too%20was%20easily%20proved%20wrong%20because%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20bar%20gene.%20Now%2C%20this%20fact%20has%20been%20admitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20regulators%20have%20failed%20either%20intentionally%2C%20or%20because%20they%20are%20simply%20unable%20to%20stop%20illegal%20(unapproved%20by%20the%20regulator)%20HT%20Bt%20cotton%20being%20grown%20on%20a%20commercial%20scale%20for%20the%20last%2015%20years%20or%20so.%20This%20is%20the%20state%20of%20GMO%20regulation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBayer%E2%80%99s%20own%20data%20sheet%20states%20that%20glufosinate%20causes%20birth%20defects%20and%20is%20damaging%20to%20most%20plants%20that%20it%20comes%20into%20contact%20with.%20Like%20its%20counterpart%20glyphosate%2C%20it%20is%20a%20systemic%2C%20broad%20spectrum%2C%20non-selective%20herbicide%20(it%20indiscriminately%20kills%20soil%20organisms%2C%20beneficial%20insects%20etc)%20and%20is%20damaging%20to%20most%20plants%20and%20aquatic%20life.%20The%20US%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20classifies%20glufosinate%20ammonium%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpersistent%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmobile%E2%80%9D%20and%20is%20%E2%80%9Cexpected%20to%20adversely%20affect%20non-target%20terrestrial%20plant%20species%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlufosinate%20is%20not%20permitted%20in%20crop%20plants%20in%20India%2C%20under%20the%20Insecticides%20Act%20(1968).%20Since%20it%20is%20very%20persistent%20in%20the%20environment%2C%20it%20will%20certainly%20contaminate%20water%20supplies%20in%20addition%20to%20food.%20Surfactants%20are%20used%20to%20get%20the%20active%20ingredients%20into%20the%20plant%2C%20which%20is%20engineered%20to%20withstand%20the%20herbicide%2C%20so%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20die%20when%20sprayed.%20The%20herbicide%20and%20surfactant%20are%20sprayed%20directly%20on%20the%20crops%20and%20significant%20quantities%20are%20then%20taken%20up%20into%20the%20plant.%C2%A0%20The%20weeds%20die%20%E2%80%94%20or%20used%20to!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Geological%20survey%20noted%20that%20while%2020%20million%20pounds%2Fyear%20of%20glyphosate%20was%20used%20prior%20to%20GE%20crops%20(1992)%2C%20280%20million%20pounds%2Fyear%20was%20used%20in%202012%2C%20largely%20as%20a%20result%20of%20glyphosate-resistant%20crops.%20In%20the%20U.S.%20alone%2C%20glyphosate-resistant%20weeds%20were%20estimated%20to%20occupy%20an%20area%20of%20over%2024%20million%20hectares%20as%20of%202012.%20This%20is%20a%20failed%20and%20unsustainable%20technology%20anywhere%2C%20and%20for%20India%20it%20will%20be%20disastrous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stated%20objective%20by%20the%20regulators%20themselves%20for%20HT%20mustard%20is%20that%20the%20two%20HT%20parent%20lines%20(barnase%20and%20barstar%20each%20with%20the%20bar%20gene)%2C%20will%20be%20similarly%20employed%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20best%20(non-GMO)%20varieties%20to%20create%20new%20crosses%20resulting%20in%20any%20number%20of%20HT%20hybrid%20mustard%20DMH%20crops.%20Thus%2C%20Indian%20mustard%20varieties%20(non-GMO)%20in%20a%20very%20short%20time%20will%20be%20contaminated%20and%20Indian%20mustard%20agriculture%20(which%20is%20non-GMO)%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regulators%20claim%20that%20GMO%20HT%20hybrid%20DMH%2011%20will%20create%20a%20significant%20dent%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20oilseeds%20imports.%20Given%20that%20GMO%20mustard%20has%20no%20gene%20for%20yield%20enhancement%20and%20is%20significantly%20out-yielded%20by%20non-GMO%20mustard%20hybrids%20and%20varieties%2C%20this%20is%20indeed%20a%20magic%20bean%20produced%20from%20thin%20air%20by%20the%20regulators%2C%20defying%20all%20logic%20and%20commonsense.%20Mustard%20oil%20imports%20are%20virtually%20zero%20(ie%20rapeseed%20mustard%20as%20distinct%20from%20canola%20rape%20oil%20which%20is%20also%20illegal%20GMO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20current%20steep%20decline%20in%20oilseeds%20production%20in%20Indian%20farming%20must%20be%20laid%20at%20the%20door%20of%20a%20wrong%20policy%20decision%20that%20comprehensively%20ignored%20national%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20interest%20to%20severely%20slash%20import%20duties%20on%20oilseeds%20of%20around%20300%25%20to%20virtually%20zero.%20In%201993-94%2C%20India%20imported%20just%203%25%20of%20our%20oil-seed%20demand%3B%20we%20were%20self-%20sufficient.%20Then%20we%20happily%20bowed%20to%20pressure%20from%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%20and%20now%20import%20almost%2070%25%20of%20our%20demand%20in%20edible%20oils%2C%20as%20per%20policy%20analyst%20Devinder%20Sharma.%20This%20is%20the%20real%20reason%20for%20our%20heavy%20import%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TEC%20recommends%20a%20double%20bar%20on%20GM%20Mustard%20%E2%80%94%20for%20being%20an%20HT%20crop%20and%20also%20in%20a%20centre%20of%20mustard%20diversification%20and%2For%20origin.%20I%20hope%20that%20our%20government%20will%20recognise%20the%20dangers%20of%20GMOs%2C%20bar%20HT%20crops%20including%20GM%20mustard%2C%20and%20impose%20a%20moratorium%20on%20all%20Bt%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAruna%20Rodrigues%20is%20the%20Lead%20Petitioner%20in%20the%20GMO%20PIL%20filed%20in%202005%20for%20a%20moratorium%20on%20GM%20crops.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708430440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20154101%2Fdietmar-kraus-qtgR-PgjVV4-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fof-magic-beans-and-modified-mustard-how-gmos-will-destroy-indian-agriculture-and-impact-health%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20introduction%20of%20Bt%20and%20HT%20crops%20will%20harm%20the%20health%20of%201%20billion%20Indians%20and%20their%20animals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fof-magic-beans-and-modified-mustard-how-gmos-will-destroy-indian-agriculture-and-impact-health%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kamal%20Nath%20May%20Stay%20or%20Go%2C%20But%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Has%20Moved%20on%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20164731%2FGGZM_qoWAAAVrez.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ERumours%20about%20former%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20his%20MP%20son%20Nakul%20Nath%20might%20be%20%E2%80%9Ca%20conspiracy%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fkamal-nath-congress-join-bjp-madhya-pradesh-congress-president-jitu-patwari-2503870-2024-02-19%5C%22%3ECongress%20has%20alleged%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20veteran%20leader%20himself%20appears%20complicit%20in%20it.%20He%20did%20not%20unequivocally%20scotch%20the%20rumours%20that%20began%20to%20swirl%20since%20the%20father-son%20duo%20suddenly%20landed%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20February%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamal%20Nath%20merely%20had%20to%20say%20that%20neither%20he%20nor%20his%20son%20was%20planning%20to%20leave%20the%20Congress%2C%20to%20clear%20the%20air.%20Instead%2C%20he%20evaded%20the%20media%20queries%2C%20neither%20confirming%20nor%20denying%20the%20rumours.%20And%20to%20add%20to%20the%20confusion%2C%20Nakul%20Nath%20dropped%20Congress%20from%20his%20social%20media%20bio%2C%20further%20fuelling%20rumours%20of%20a%20potential%20switch%20by%20the%20father-son%20duo.%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20staunch%20supporter%20and%20former%20minister%20Sajjan%20Singh%20Verma%20also%20removed%20Congress%20from%20his%20social%20media%20bio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDenials%20by%20Congress%20leaders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20intriguing%20reticence%20from%20the%20father-son%20duo%2C%20Congress%20leaders%20from%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20to%20Jitu%20Patwari%20stoutly%20denied%20the%20possibility%20of%20defection.%20Digvijaya%20Singh%2C%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20long-time%20Congress%20colleague%2C%20was%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20try%20and%20stop%20the%20former%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20from%20breaking%20ranks.%20Singh%20talked%20to%20Nath%20at%20least%20three%20times%20during%20the%20intervening%20night%20of%20February%2018%20and%2019.%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Congress%20president%20Patwari%20too%20joined%20the%20efforts%20to%20dissuade%20Kamal%20Nath%20from%20jumping%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20rumours%20that%20Kamal%20Nath%20is%20going%20to%20BJP%2C%20this%20is%20an%20example%20of%20how%20media%20can%20be%20misused.%20This%20was%20a%20conspiracy%20made%20against%20Kamal%20Nath.%20I%20spoke%20to%20him%20and%20he%20said%20that%20all%20these%20things%20are%20just%20rumours%2C%E2%80%9D%20Patwari%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20spoke%20to%20him%20and%20he%20said%20that%20all%20these%20things%20are%20just%20rumours%2C%20and%20he%20is%20a%20Congress%20person%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20Congress%20person.%20He%20will%20continue%20to%20have%20Congress%20ideology%20till%20his%20last%20breath.%20These%20are%20his%20own%20thoughts%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20suspense%20about%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20future%20move%20persisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20on%20February%2019%20that%20the%20rumours%20abated%20%E2%80%93%20though%20were%20not%20cleared%20fully%20%E2%80%93%20when%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20acolyte%20Sajjan%20Singh%20Verma%20asserted%20that%20his%20leader%20would%20stay%20put%20in%20the%20Congress.%20The%20assertion%20followed%20his%20meeting%20with%20Kamal%20Nath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20Congress%20general%20secretary%20in%20charge%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Jitendra%20Singh%20dismissed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmisinformation%E2%80%9D%20the%20speculation%20over%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20switch%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20asserted%20that%20the%20veteran%20leader%20will%20participate%20in%20the%20Rahul%20Gandhi-led%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20vulnerability%20exposed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20for%20now%2C%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Nakul%20Nath%20are%20with%20the%20Congress.%20However%2C%20the%20speculations%20surrounding%20the%C2%A0nine-time%20MP%20from%20Chhindwara%20have%20accentuated%20the%20rumours%20of%20his%20vulnerability%20to%20joining%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20future%2C%20either%20owing%20to%20his%20ambitions%20to%20chart%20a%20political%20course%20outside%20the%20weakening%20Congress%20or%20to%20safeguard%20his%20business%20interests.%20The%20former%20chief%20minister%20knows%20only%20too%20well%20that%20despite%20his%20vehement%20claims%20of%20innocence%2C%20he%20is%20not%20out%20of%20the%20woods%20for%20his%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20the%201984%20anti-Sikh%20violence.%20The%20matter%20is%20still%20in%20court%20for%20adjudication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20he%20is%20aware%20he%20could%20more%20easily%20safeguard%20his%20business%20interests%20from%20the%20prying%20eyes%20of%20the%20sleuths%20of%20the%20CBI%2C%20IT%20and%20ED%20only%20if%20he%20is%20aligned%20with%20the%20ruling%20party%20at%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20septuagenarian%20leader%20appears%20more%20worried%20about%20the%20political%20future%20of%20his%20son%20than%20his%20own.%20Nakul%20Nath%20somehow%20managed%20to%20retain%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20Chhindwara%20bastion%20for%20the%20Congress%20with%20a%20considerably%20reduced%20margin%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20Nakul%20Nath%20was%20the%20lone%20Congress%20winner%20in%20all%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20while%20all%20the%20remaining%2028%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20kitty.%20For%20the%20coming%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20appears%20hellbent%20on%20snatching%20from%20the%20Congress%20the%20Chhindwara%20seat%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%20eyes%20Chhindwara%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20all%20seven%20MLAs%20under%20the%20Chhindwara%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20had%20won%20on%20a%20Congress%20ticket%20in%20the%20December%202023%20assembly%20election%2C%20and%20all%20of%20them%20are%20his%20staunch%20loyalists%2C%20Kamal%20Nath%20seems%20unsure%20of%20banking%20on%20the%20seemingly%20rosy%20political%20calculus%20for%20his%20son%20to%20retain%20the%20pocket%20borough%20in%20the%20coming%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20T%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ehe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20relentless%20efforts%20to%20penetrate%20the%20lone%20Congress%20bastion%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20seem%20to%20have%20unnerved%20the%20father-son%20duo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMarginalised%20after%20poll%20debacle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamal%20Nath%20might%20not%20have%20toyed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20switching%20over%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20all-out%20efforts%20to%20storm%20the%20Chhindwara%20fortress%20had%20he%20been%20assured%20of%20his%20continued%20and%20complete%20sway%20over%20the%20state%20Congress.%20The%20unexpected%20Congress%20debacle%20in%20the%20recently%20held%20assembly%20elections%20has%20diminished%20his%20political%20clout%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20the%20veteran%20leader%20was%20not%20even%20consulted%20on%20the%20appointment%20of%20his%20successor%20Patwari%20as%20the%20state%20Congress%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Patwari%20is%20as%20deferential%20to%20Kamal%20Nath%20after%20assuming%20his%20new%20responsibility%20as%20before%2C%20the%20state%20Congress%20organisation%20has%20come%20out%20of%20the%20former%20chief%E2%80%99s%20overwhelming%20shadow%20sooner%20than%20he%20may%20have%20imagined.%20Photographs%20of%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20are%20conspicuously%20missing%20in%20the%20banners%20and%20posters%20of%20the%20state%20Congress.%20While%20Digvijaya%20Singh%20seems%20to%20have%20reconciled%20to%20the%20changed%20political%20dynamics%20in%20the%20Congress%2C%20Kamal%20Nath%20is%20reported%20to%20be%20uneasy%20in%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20emerging%20reality%20where%20he%20is%20being%20regarded%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Congress%20version%20of%20%E2%80%9CMarg%20Darshak%20mandal.%E2%80%9D%20He%20seems%20loathe%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20being%20treated%20as%20an%20L.K.%20Advani%20in%20the%20organisation%20which%20he%20ran%20as%20the%20unquestionable%20supreme%20boss%20from%20April%202017%20to%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChequered%20innings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20six-year%20period%20saw%20many%20highs%20and%20lows%20for%20Kamal%20Nath%3B%20he%20led%20the%20Congress%20to%20victory%20in%20the%202018%20election%3B%20his%20government%20fell%2015%20months%20later%20owing%20to%20a%20revolt%20by%20his%20bete-noire%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%3B%20and%2C%20finally%2C%20the%20shocking%20defeat%20in%20the%202023%20polls%20where%20the%20Congress%20tally%20came%20down%20from%20114%20in%20the%20previous%20election%20to%20just%2066%20out%20of%20the%20230%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defeat%20in%20the%20assembly%20election%20shook%20the%20state%20Congress%20to%20the%20core.%20While%20the%20leaders%20publicly%20blamed%20it%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%20%E2%80%93%20some%20plausible%20and%20some%20ridiculous%20%E2%80%93%20among%20the%20cadres%20a%20near%20consensus%20emerged%20that%20the%20impervious%20and%20imperious%20leadership%20of%20Kamal%20Nath%20did%20the%20Congress%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20felt%20that%20the%20then%20PCC%20chief%E2%80%99s%20dalliance%20with%20Hindutva%20damaged%20the%20Congress%20prospects%20in%20no%20small%20measure.%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20genuflection%20before%20dubious%20%E2%80%9CBabas%E2%80%9D%20such%20as%20Dhirendra%20Shastri%20and%20Pradeep%20Mishra%20and%20his%20flaunting%20the%20self-image%20of%20a%20Hanuman%20Bhakt%20only%20furthered%20the%20cause%20of%20Hindutva%2C%20much%20to%20the%20delight%20and%20benefit%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnsurprisingly%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20ordinary%20Congress%20worker%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20is%20more%20curious%20than%20worried%20about%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20son%E2%80%99s%20politics.%20He%20wishes%20the%20Congress%20move%20on%20after%20the%20assembly%20defeat%20and%20celebrate%20rather%20than%20lament%20the%20disappearance%20of%20Kamal%20Nath%20from%20its%20arena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIdeology-neutral%20Kamal%20Nath%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESure%20enough%2C%20Congress%20workers%20have%20never%20had%20any%20delusion%20about%20the%20businessman-politician%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20ideology.%20Ever%20since%20he%20became%20Lok%20Sabha%20member%20from%20Chhindwara%20in%201980%2C%20the%20entry%20of%20the%20Kolkata-based%20industrialist%20in%20the%20MP%20Congress%20scenario%20spawned%20gossip%20about%20his%20riches%2C%20his%20go-getter%20persona%2C%20his%20proximity%20to%20the%20Gandhi%20family%20and%20his%20proficiency%20in%20back-room%20strategies.%20But%2C%20unlike%20Digvijaya%20Singh%2C%20his%20peer%20and%20long-time%20friend%20was%20never%20seen%20as%20a%20believer%20in%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20ideology%2C%20particularly%20secularism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20Kamal%20Nath%20was%20in%20central%20politics%20while%20assiduously%20nurturing%20his%20Chhindwara%20constituency%2C%20his%20ideology%20didn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20much%20for%20the%20Congress%20workers.%20But%20his%20ambivalence%20to%20secularism%20as%20spearhead%20of%20the%20state%20Congress%20in%20the%20two%20assembly%20elections%20was%20noticed%20in%20the%20cadres%20with%20disapproval%2C%20albeit%20muted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20chastened%20Congress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20realised%20how%20it%20paid%20a%20heavy%20prize%20for%20competing%20with%20the%20BJP%20on%20the%20Hindutva%20pitch%20in%20the%20assembly%20election%2C%20a%20chastened%20state%20Congress%20seems%20to%20have%20no%20space%20for%20either%20Kamal%20Nath%20or%20his%20brand%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20stand%20to%20lose%20much%2C%20should%20Kamal%20Nath%20leave%20the%20party%20with%20a%20few%20MLAs%20in%20tow.%20That%20will%20not%20alter%20the%20basic%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%20in%20the%20assembly.%20The%20next%20assembly%20election%20is%20due%20in%202028%20and%20by%20then%20political%20dynamics%20will%20have%20changed%20unpredictably.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20coming%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20is%20concerned%2C%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20get%20worse%20for%20the%20party%20which%20had%20lost%2028%20out%20of%2029%20seats.%20If%20Nakul%20Nath%20stays%20in%20the%20Congress%2C%20he%20is%20sure%20to%20be%20renominated%20as%20the%20candidate%20from%20Chhindwara.%20If%20he%20opts%20to%20become%20the%20BJP%20candidate%2C%20the%20Congress%20will%20have%20one%20more%20seat%20to%20fight%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnencumbered%20of%20Kamal%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20political%20legacy%2C%20the%20state%20Congress%20has%20an%20opportunity%20to%20restore%20inner-party%20democracy%20in%20the%20organisation%20where%20ordinary%20workers%20can%20become%20enthusiastic%20stakeholders%20in%20shaping%20its%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708430418000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20164731%2FGGZM_qoWAAAVrez.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkamal-nath-may-stay-or-go-but-the-madhya-pradesh-congress-has-moved-on%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20now%2C%20Kamal%20Nath%20and%20Nakul%20Nath%20are%20with%20the%20Congress.%20However%2C%20the%20speculations%20surrounding%20the%C2%A0nine-time%20MP%20from%20Chhindwara%20have%20accentuated%20the%20rumours%20of%20his%20vulnerability%20to%20joining%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20future%2C%20either%20owing%20to%20his%20ambitions%20to%20chart%20a%20political%20course%20outside%20the%20weakening%20Congress%20or%20to%20safeguard%20his%20business%20interests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkamal-nath-may-stay-or-go-but-the-madhya-pradesh-congress-has-moved-on%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20simple%20lifestyle%20changes%20that%20could%20cut%20the%20risk%20of%20irritable%20bowel%20syndrome%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708430040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-stomach-pain-stomach_6400348.jpg%3F20231221092438%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firritable-bowel-syndrome-the-simple-lifestyle-changes-that-could-cut-the-risk-of-developing-condition-13076143%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Simple%20everyday%20lifestyle%20changes%20could%20cut%20the%20risk%20of%20irritable%20bowel%20syndrome%20(IBS)%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20long-term%20study.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firritable-bowel-syndrome-the-simple-lifestyle-changes-that-could-cut-the-risk-of-developing-condition-13076143%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firritable-bowel-syndrome-the-simple-lifestyle-changes-that-could-cut-the-risk-of-developing-condition-13076143%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firritable-bowel-syndrome-the-simple-lifestyle-changes-that-could-cut-the-risk-of-developing-condition-13076143%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blow%20to%20BJP%20as%20Supreme%20Court%20Declares%20AAP-Congress%20Candidate%20Winner%20of%20Chandigarh%20Mayoral%20Poll%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20a%20major%20blow%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20during%20a%20resumed%20hearing%20on%20the%20controversial%20Chandigarh%20mayoral%20election%20declared%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%E2%80%99s%20Kuldeep%20Kumar%20the%20validly%20elected%20mayor%20of%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20municipal%20corporation%20on%20Tuesday%20(February%2020).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20after%20the%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20ruled%20that%20the%20election%E2%80%99s%20presiding%20officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20made%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20deface%20eight%20ballots%20that%20were%20cast%20in%20favour%20of%20Kumar%20so%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Manoj%20Sonkar%20was%20declared%20the%20elected%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYesterday%2C%20the%20presiding%20officer%20made%20a%20solemn%20statement%20before%20this%20court%20that%20he%20had%20done%20so%20as%20the%20eight%20ballots%20were%20defaced.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20none%20of%20the%20ballots%20are%20defaced%20%5Bbefore%20Masih%20made%20markings%20on%20them%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said%20after%20it%20examined%20the%20defaced%20ballots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20bench%2C%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20presiding%20officer%20has%20to%20be%20deprecated%20at%20two%20levels.%20First%2C%20he%20has%20unlawfully%20altered%20the%20course%20of%20the%20mayoral%20election.%20Second%2C%20in%20making%20a%20solemn%20statement%20before%20the%20court%20on%20Monday%20(February%2019)%2C%20the%20presiding%20officer%20expressed%20falsehood%20for%20which%20he%20must%20be%20held%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20above%20reasons%2C%20we%20have%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20results%20declared%20by%20the%20presiding%20officer%20are%20unlawful%20and%20have%20to%20be%20set%20aside%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20taking%20stern%20action%20against%20Masih%2C%20the%20bench%20ruled%20that%20a%20fit%20case%20is%20made%20out%20for%20the%20initiation%20of%20proceedings%20under%20Section%20340%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20court-monitored%20inquiries%2C%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRegistrar%20Judicial%20is%20directed%20to%20issue%20a%20notice%20to%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20to%20show%20cause%20as%20to%20why%20steps%20should%20not%20be%20initiated%20against%20him%20under%20Section%20340%20CrPC%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20ruled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMasih%20was%20also%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Chandigarh%20minority%20cell.%20After%20the%20controversy%20surrounding%20the%20mayoral%20election%2C%20he%20was%20taken%20down%20from%20the%20post%20on%20February%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESC%20says%20no%20to%20fresh%20election%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20Masih%2C%20the%20solicitor%20general%20had%20sought%20fresh%20polls%2C%20which%20the%20BJP%20ideally%20wanted%20as%20it%20had%20already%20inducted%20three%20AAP%20councillors%20into%20its%20fold%20in%20order%20to%20muster%20enough%20numbers%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20re-poll.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20against%20this%2C%20with%20the%20bench%20stating%20it%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20setting%20aside%20the%20entire%20election%20process%20is%20inappropriate%20as%20the%20only%20infirmity%20was%20found%20in%20the%20counting%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetting%20aside%20the%20entire%20election%20process%20will%20compound%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20democratic%20principles%20that%20occurred%20due%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20presiding%20officer%2C%20it%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20bench%2C%20the%20court%20is%20duty%20bound%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20democratic%20process%20is%20not%20set%20at%20naught%20by%20such%20subterfuge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20therefore%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20court%20must%20step%20in%20such%20exceptional%20circumstances%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20basic%20democratic%20mandate%20is%20ensured%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECongress%2C%20AAP%20hail%20SC%20order%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20reaction%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20AAP%20supremo%20and%20Delhi%20chief%20minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20thanked%20the%20court%20for%20saving%20democracy%20in%20these%20difficult%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20congratulated%20Kumar%20and%20said%20that%20he%20hails%20from%20a%20poor%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20victory%20became%20possible%20because%20of%20the%20SC.%20This%20is%20a%20victory%20of%20Indian%20democracy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kejriwal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20statement%2C%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20saved%20democracy%20from%20the%20fangs%20of%20an%20autocratic%20BJP%2C%20which%20resorted%20to%20dirty%20election%20manipulation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20institutional%20sabotage%20in%20the%20Chandigarh%20mayor%20polls%20is%20only%20a%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg%20in%20Modi-Shah%E2%80%99s%20devious%20conspiracy%20to%20trample%20democracy.%20All%20Indians%20must%20fight%20this%20onslaught%20on%20our%20constitution%2C%20collectively.%20Never%20forget.%20Our%20democracy%20shall%20be%20at%20the%20crossroads%20in%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections!%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20reacted%20by%20saying%20that%20Masih%20was%20just%20a%20pawn%20in%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20murder%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20president%20J.P.%20Nadda%20had%20earlier%20said%20of%20Sonkar%E2%80%99s%20victory%20that%20it%20showed%20how%20the%20INDIA%20political%20bloc%2C%20of%20which%20both%20the%20Congress%20and%20AAP%20are%20part%20of%2C%20was%20not%20working%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20the%20INDI%20Alliance%20fought%20their%20first%20electoral%20battle%20and%20still%20lost%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20BJP%20shows%20that%20neither%20their%20arithmetic%20is%20working%20nor%20their%20chemistry%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJPNadda%2Fstatus%2F1752241512560341137%5C%22%3ENadda%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20congratulating%20Sonkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Masih%20made%20the%20BJP%20candidate%20the%20winner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20for%20the%20post%20of%20mayor%20was%20conducted%20on%20January%2030.%20Two%20candidates%20were%20in%20the%20fray%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKuldeep%20Kumar%20was%20a%20candidate%20set%20up%20in%20an%20alliance%20between%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress.%20The%20BJP%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20fielded%20Manoj%20Sonkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirty-five%20councillors%20as%20well%20as%20Chandigarh%E2%80%99s%20MP%20were%20eligible%20to%20vote%20during%20the%20mayoral%20election%2C%20taking%20the%20total%20number%20of%20eligible%20voters%20to%2036.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElection%20to%20the%20post%20of%20mayor%20is%20governed%20by%20the%20Chandigarh%20Municipal%20Corporation%20(Procedure%20and%20Conduct%20of%20Business)%20Regulations%2C%201996%20and%20is%20held%20by%20secret%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20was%20the%20favourite%20to%20win%2C%20since%20both%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress%20had%20total%20of%2020%20councillors%20(13%20of%20the%20AAP%20and%20seven%20of%20the%20Congress)%2C%20while%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20maximum%20strength%20was%2015%20votes%20including%20one%20vote%20from%20the%20Chandigarh%20BJP%20MP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Masih%20declared%20as%20many%20as%20eight%20votes%20of%20AAP%20and%20Congress%20councillors%20invalid%2C%20thereby%20declaring%20Sonkar%20as%20the%20new%20Chandigarh%20mayor%2C%20who%20won%20the%20election%20by%2016%20votes%20to%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20proceedings%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20prove%20beyond%20doubt%20that%20Masih%20had%20deliberately%20rigged%20eight%20opposition%20votes%20to%20favour%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Sonkar%2C%20who%20has%20already%20resigned%20from%20the%20post%20on%20Sunday%20while%20apprehending%20stern%20action%20from%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Masih%20had%20evidently%20marked%20the%20ballots%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20treating%20them%20as%20invalid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20has%20acted%20beyond%20his%20remit%20of%20statutory%20regulations%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20declaring%20Kumar%20as%20the%20new%20Chandigarh%20mayor%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20that%20the%20ink%20marks%20placed%20by%20Masih%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20ballots%20have%20no%20consequence%20and%20that%20these%20votes%20would%20therefore%20be%20treated%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428824000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fblow-to-bjp-as-supreme-court-declares-aap-candidate-winner-of-chandigarh-mayoral-poll%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bench%20ordered%20an%20inquiry%20against%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20the%20election's%20presiding%20officer%20and%20a%20former%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20BJP's%20Chandigarh%20minority%20cell%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20spoke%20falsehoods%20in%20his%20statements%20to%20the%20apex%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A56%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fblow-to-bjp-as-supreme-court-declares-aap-candidate-winner-of-chandigarh-mayoral-poll%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israeli%20Advance%20on%20Rafah%20Would%20Have%20%E2%80%98Dire%20Humanitarian%20Consequences%E2%80%99%3A%20Senior%20Gaza%20Official%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20163806%2Fimage1170x530croppe.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20extension%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20operation%20in%20Rafah%2C%20where%20over%20a%20million%20internally%20displaced%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20shelter%2C%20will%20have%20%E2%80%9Cdire%20humanitarian%20consequences%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20UN%20Senior%20Humanitarian%20Coordinator%20for%20Gaza%2C%20Sigrid%20Kaag%2C%20said%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaag%20reiterated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2F%5C%22%3ESecretary-General%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20concern%20that%20such%20an%20operation%20at%20present%20time%20would%20be%20potentially%20disastrous%20for%20innocent%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people%20crammed%20in%20Rafah.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20intended%20for%20a%20million%20people%20in%20shelters%2C%20in%20random%20sort%20of%20plastic%20sheeted%20constructions.%20Health%20conditions%20are%20very%20worrisome%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20correspondents%20in%20Brussels%20after%20briefing%20European%20Union%20foreign%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20voiced%20deep%20concern%20over%20getting%20aid%20into%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20and%20distributing%20it%20to%20those%20in%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20security%20conditions%2C%20separate%20from%20military%20operations%2C%20due%20to%20what%20is%20called%20self-distribution%20by%20desperate%20civilians%2C%20but%20also%20looting%20and%20criminalisation%2C%20is%20hampering%20efforts%20by%20the%20humanitarian%20community%E2%80%A6to%20deliver%20assistance%20to%20the%20people%20that%20actually%20need%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20needs%20to%20be%20done%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20on%20Monday%2C%20UN%20Special%20Coordinator%20for%20the%20Middle%20East%20Peace%20Process%2C%20Tor%20Wennesland%2C%20visited%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20where%20he%20met%20with%20internally%20displaced%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20met%20with%20NGO%20and%20UN%20personnel%20the%20see%20the%20challenges%20they%20face%20first%20hand%2C%20including%20the%20breakdown%20of%20law%20and%20order%20which%20is%20impacting%20the%20distribution%20of%20humanitarian%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20clear%20that%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20UN%20Spokesperson%20Stephane%20Dujarric%20told%20correspondents%20in%20New%20York%20at%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsg%2Fen%2Fcontent%2Fossg%2Fnoon-briefing-highlight%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20press%20briefing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20UN%20needs%20the%20tools%20to%20deliver%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20including%20the%20need%20for%20Israel%20to%20allow%20entry%20of%20items%20critical%20to%20UN%20operations%20and%20to%20improve%20deconfliction%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContinued%20hostilities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntense%20Israeli%20bombardment%20from%20air%2C%20land%20and%20sea%20continues%20across%20much%20of%20the%20war-torn%20enclave%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UN%20Office%20for%20the%20Coordination%20of%20Humanitarian%20Affairs%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unocha.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOCHA%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20resulting%20in%20further%20civilian%20casualties%2C%20displacement%2C%20and%20destruction%20of%20civilian%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWidespread%20ground%20operations%20and%20heavy%20fighting%20between%20Israeli%20forces%20and%20Palestinian%20armed%20groups%20also%20continue%20to%20be%20reported%2C%20especially%20in%20Khan%20Younis%20and%20Deir%20al%20Balah%2C%20OCHA%20said%20in%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fcontent%2Fhostilities-gaza-strip-and-israel-flash-update-121%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflash%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%2017%20and%2019%20February%2C%20dozens%20of%20rockets%20were%20also%20reportedly%20fired%20by%20armed%20Palestinians%20toward%20Israel%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENasser%20hospital%20evacuations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20Israeli%20military%20operation%20in%20the%20Nasser%20Hospital%20complex%20in%20Khan%20Younis%20have%20continued%2C%20OCHA%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20UN%20and%20the%20Palestine%20Red%20Crescent%20Society%20evacuated%2014%20patients.%20Negotiations%20are%20ongoing%20for%20the%20evacuation%20of%20the%20remaining%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20UN%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWHO%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20over%20180%20patients%20and%2015%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20remain%20inside%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hospital%20is%20still%20experiencing%20an%20acute%20shortage%20of%20food%2C%20basic%20medical%20supplies%2C%20and%20oxygen.%20There%20is%20no%20tap%20water%20and%20no%20electricity%2C%20except%20a%20backup%20generator%20maintaining%20some%20lifesaving%20machines%2C%E2%80%9D%20WHO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Steep%20rise%E2%80%99%20in%20child%20malnutrition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUN%20agencies%20on%20Monday%20warned%20of%20a%20steep%20rise%20in%20malnutrition%20among%20children%20and%20pregnant%20and%20breastfeeding%20women%2C%20posing%20grave%20threat%20to%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20especially%20serious%20in%20north%20Gaza%2C%20which%20has%20been%20almost%20completely%20cut%20off%20from%20aid%20for%20weeks%2C%20and%20where%20one%20in%20six%20children%20under%20the%20age%20of%20two%20is%20acutely%20malnourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20not%20much%20better%20in%20southern%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20UN%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUNICEF%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20WHO%20and%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%20(WFP)%2C%20said%20in%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2Fpress-releases%2Fchildrens-lives-threatened-rising-malnutrition-gaza-strip%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rafah%2C%20where%20aid%20has%20been%20more%20available%2C%205%25%20of%20children%20under%20two%20are%20acutely%20malnourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20clear%20evidence%20that%20access%20to%20humanitarian%20aid%20is%20needed%20and%20can%20help%20prevent%20the%20worst%20outcomes%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agencies%20said%2C%20reiterating%20the%20call%20to%20protect%20Rafah%20from%20the%20threat%20of%20intensified%20military%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWest%20Bank%20violence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOCHA%20also%20reported%20further%20violent%20incidents%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20claiming%20both%20Israeli%20and%20Palestinian%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%2016%20February%2C%20two%20Israeli%20men%20were%20shot%20and%20killed%20in%20southern%20Israel%2C%20and%20four%20others%20including%20a%20child%20were%20injured%2C%20by%20a%20Palestinian%20man%20from%20Shu%E2%80%99fat%20refugee%20camp%20in%20East%20Jerusalem.%20The%20Palestinian%20man%20was%20then%20shot%20and%20killed%20by%20an%20armed%20Israeli%20civilian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20Israeli%20forces%20killed%20two%20Palestinian%20men%20in%20Tulkarm%20Refugee%20camp%2C%20during%20an%20exchange%20of%20fire%20with%20a%20Palestinian%20man%20whose%20body%20was%20later%20withheld%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20from%20being%20handed%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20fatality%20was%20an%20unarmed%20Palestinian%20who%20was%20reportedly%20killed%20by%20an%20Israeli%20army%20sniper%20while%20standing%20on%20the%20rooftop%20of%20his%20house%2C%20OCHA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20October%207%2C%202023%20and%20February%2018%2C%20393%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20including%20100%20children%2C%20and%204%2C511%20Palestinians%2C%20including%20699%20children%2C%20have%20been%20injured%20in%20conflict-related%20incidents%20across%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20including%20East%20Jerusalem%2C%20and%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20same%20period%2C%2012%20Israelis%2C%20including%20four%20members%20of%20Israeli%20forces%2C%20were%20killed%20and%2080%20injured%20in%20conflict-related%20incidents%20in%20the%20same%20areas%2C%20according%20to%20OCHA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorld%20Court%20asked%20for%20legal%20opinion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20at%20the%20Peace%20Palace%20in%20The%20Hague%2C%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EICJ%3C%2Fa%3E)%20is%20holding%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fnode%2F203551%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehearing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0concerning%20an%20advisory%20opinion%20on%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments.un.org%2Fdoc%2Fundoc%2Fgen%2Fn23%2F004%2F68%2Fpdf%2Fn2300468.pdf%3Ftoken%3Dd0pFjUBDEHpx8llwLn%26fe%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELegal%20Consequences%20arising%20from%20the%20Policies%20and%20Practices%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territory%2C%20including%20East%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advisory%2C%20non-binding%2C%20opinion%20on%20the%20occupation%20was%20requested%20by%20the%20General%20Assembly%20in%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearings%20will%20be%20held%20from%2019%20to%2026%20February%2C%20with%20over%2050%20countries%2C%20groups%20and%20the%20State%20of%20Palestine%20scheduled%20to%20speak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2024%2F02%2F1146672%5C%22%3EUN%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428762000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20163806%2Fimage1170x530croppe.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-advance-on-rafah-would-have-dire-humanitarian-consequences-senior-gaza-official%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'There%20are%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people%20crammed%20in%20Rafah.%20It's%20not%20intended%20for%20a%20million%20people%20in%20shelters%2C%20in%20random%20sort%20of%20plastic%20sheeted%20constructions.%20Health%20conditions%20are%20very%20worrisome%2C'%20said%20UN%20Senior%20Humanitarian%20Coordinator%20for%20Gaza%20Sigrid%20Kaag.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%