ings-Valley.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20article%20in%20Hindi%20by%20my%20father%2C%20the%20late%20Kailash%20Vajpeyi%20(d.%202015)%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3E%C4%80sth%C4%81%20men%3Cem%3E%20R%C4%81m%E2%80%9D%2C%20first%20appeared%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3EKadambini%3Cem%3E%20magazine%20in%20April%202013.%20The%20piece%20was%20republished%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024%2C%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3EHindustan%3Cem%3E%20newspaper.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%20decided%20to%20translate%20it%20for%20an%20English%20language%20readership%20because%20it%20describes%20an%20approach%20to%20the%20deity%20Ram%2C%20to%20his%20worship%20and%20to%20the%20literature%20centred%20around%20him%20(mainly%20the%20Sanskrit%20epic%20by%20Valmiki%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3ER%C4%81m%C4%81ya%E1%B9%87a%3Cem%3E%2C%20and%20the%20medieval%20Awadh%C4%AB%20epic%20poem%20by%20Tulsidas%2C%20the%3C%2Fem%3E%20R%C4%81mcaritm%C4%81nas%3Cem%3E)%2C%20in%20terms%20that%20would%20surely%20appeal%20to%20most%20devotees%20and%20believers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20scholars%20and%20historians.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20beauty%2C%20compassion%20and%20erudition%20evident%20in%20this%20short%20essay%20provide%20a%20sharp%20counterpoint%20to%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20Ram%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20reimagined%20and%20represented%20today.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20story%20of%20Ram%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3ER%C4%81makath%C4%81%3Cem%3E%2C%20has%20been%20central%20to%20the%20religious%2C%20literary%20and%20political%20imagination%20of%20India%20for%20at%20least%20two%20millennia%2C%20across%20many%20languages%2C%20and%20continues%20to%20enjoy%20a%20comparable%20if%20not%20a%20greater%20centrality%20in%20our%20own%20time.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBut%20the%20figure%20of%20this%20familiar%20and%20revered%20god%20has%20been%20reinscribed%20in%20Ayodhya%20at%20the%20new%20temple%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024%20in%20a%20form%20that%20goes%20against%20everything%20we%20have%20known%20and%20loved%20about%20him%20for%20centuries.%20A%20reminder%20of%20the%20true%20Ram%20we%20are%20in%20danger%C2%A0of%20forgetting%20seemed%20in%20order.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%20am%20grateful%20to%20Imre%20Bangha%20and%20Jack%20Hawley%20for%20helping%20me%20to%20translate%20poem%20111%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9CKeshav%20kahi%20na%20j%C4%81ye%2C%20k%C4%81%C2%A0kahiye%E2%80%9D%3Cem%3E)%20from%20Tulsidas%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20Vinay%20Patrik%C4%81%3Cem%3E%2C%20quoted%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20article%2C%20with%20some%20help%20from%20an%20earlier%20translation%20by%20F.R.%20Allchin.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%20have%20been%20bold%20enough%20to%20use%20my%20own%20words%20to%20render%20it%20in%20English%2C%20knowing%20that%20many%20readers%20will%20recognise%20the%20poem%20in%20the%20original%20anyway%20and%20understand%20full%20well%20how%20important%20it%20is%20in%20the%20literature%20and%20criticism%20around%20Tulsidas%E2%80%99s%20unparalleled%20oeuvre.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20a%20curious%20choice%20for%20my%20father%20to%20cite%20this%20poem%2C%20since%20its%20esoteric%20imagery%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3ENirgun%3Cem%3E%20poetry%20of%20Kabir%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3ESagun%20bhakti%3Cem%3E%20of%20Tulsidas%20himself.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Findian-civilisation-is-being-disrobed-in-the-city-of-ram%5C%22%3EIndian%20Civilisation%20Is%20Being%20Disrobed%20in%20the%20City%20of%20Ram%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20article%20also%20ends%20with%20Kabir%2C%C2%A0swerving%20away%C2%A0somewhat%20abruptly%20from%20the%20preceding%20text.%20To%20my%20mind%2C%20this%20hints%20at%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20own%20preference%20for%20a%20rather%20more%20abstract%2C%20philosophical%20and%20universal%20symbol%20of%20Ram%20than%20the%20epic%20protagonist%2C%20divine%20king%20and%20idealised%20hero%20who%20emerges%20from%20the%20narrative%20poetry%20of%20Valmiki%20and%20Tulsidas.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBut%20whatever%20our%20own%20inclination%2C%20between%20a%20sagun%20Ram%20or%20a%20nirgun%20Ram%2C%20Tulsi%E2%80%99s%20Ram%20or%20Kabir%E2%80%99s%20Ram%20(or%20indeed%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Ram%2C%20who%20is%20capacious%20enough%20to%20embrace%20religious%20difference%20and%20embody%20a%20secular%20vision)%2C%20it%20is%20important%20that%20we%20reclaim%20the%20personal%20god%2C%20literary%20character%20and%20ethical%20ideal%20come%20down%20to%20us%20under%20the%20sign%20of%20Ram.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKailash%C2%A0Vajpeyi%E2%80%99s%20sensibility%20reminds%20us%20of%20the%20broad%20and%20deep%20reservoir%20of%20Indian%20faith%2C%20with%20sweet%20waters%20flowing%20in%20from%20many%20diverse%20traditions%20of%20poetry%20and%20devotion.%20Ram%20cannot%20be%20imprisoned%20in%20narrow%20walls.%20He%20is%20born%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20believer%2C%20and%20dwells%20there%20for%20all%20eternity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnanya%C2%A0Vajpeyi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERam%20in%20our%20Faith%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKailash%C2%A0Vajpeyi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3E%C4%81sth%C4%81%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9Cfaith%E2%80%9D)%20straightaway%20signifies%20devotion%2C%20reverence%20and%20an%20attitude%20of%20surrender.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20born%20unmarked.%20But%20over%20time%2C%20experience%20leaves%20its%20traces%20on%20the%20blank%20slate%20of%20the%20self.%20Deep%20within%20us%20there%20begins%20to%20arise%20a%20symbol%2C%20planted%20like%20a%20seed%20in%20our%20consciousness%2C%20spreading%20a%20diffuse%20fragrance%2C%20dream-like%2C%20rocked%20gently%20by%20the%20waves%20of%20our%20innermost%20being.%20Clouds%20gather%20in%20the%20environment%20that%20surrounds%20us%2C%20and%20their%20soft%20rain%20nurtures%20this%20seed%2C%20watering%20it%20steadily%20until%20it%20blossoms%20forth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20time%2C%20we%20become%20transfixed%20by%20the%20colour%20and%20form%20of%20that%20which%20has%20flowered%20within%2C%20rapt%20in%20the%20beauty%20of%20its%20full-blown%20petals%2C%20and%20then%2C%20spontaneously%2C%20there%20bursts%20forth%20from%20our%20lips%2C%20a%20prayer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20form%20it%20takes%20could%20be%20anything%2C%20it%20does%20not%20matter.%20It%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20logical%20interpretation.%20All%20that%20can%20be%20said%20is%20that%20the%20essence%20of%20this%20prayer%20arising%20from%20deep%20within%20us%20is%20a%20short%2C%20sweet%20and%20pleasing%20word%3A%20%E2%80%9CRam%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20name%20blended%20effortlessly%20into%20the%20lives%20of%20millions%20of%20people%2C%20sheltering%20us%20like%20the%20ageless%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fiqbal-gandhi-rediscovering-rama-means-indians%5C%22%3EFrom%20Iqbal%20to%20Gandhi%2C%20Rediscovering%20What%20Rama%20Means%20for%20Indians%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20sky%2C%20this%20name%20has%20no%20history.%20Like%20the%20sky%2C%20it%20is%20always%20there%2C%20we%20are%20never%20parted%20from%20it.%20It%20is%20blue%2C%20like%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Ram%20is%20no%20empty%20signifier!%20The%20word%20courses%20like%20blood%20through%20our%20body%2C%20beats%20like%20the%20heart%20in%20our%20breast.%20It%20can%20be%20called%20with%20a%20thousand%20different%20names.%20It%20is%20the%20breath%20of%20our%20breath.%20We%20come%20to%20realise%20its%20greatness%20when%20at%20the%20mere%20utterance%20of%20it%2C%20our%20difficulties%20fall%20to%20pieces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20say%20how%20many%20poets%2C%20inspired%20by%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20towering%20personality%2C%20have%20sung%20paeans%20to%20their%20deity%3B%20how%20many%20sculptors%20have%20carved%20their%20deity%E2%80%99s%20face%20from%20stone.%20But%20the%20epic%20poets%20Valmiki%20and%20Vyas%20are%20the%20two%20eyes%20of%20our%20cultural%20history%2C%20representing%20two%20points%20of%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20one%20perspective%2C%20the%20ultimate%20protagonist%20is%20Sri%20Ram%2C%20and%20from%20the%20other%2C%20it%20is%20Sri%20Krishna.%20The%20two%20visionary%20poets%2C%20with%20their%20intellectual%20creativity%2C%20have%20established%20through%20their%20respective%20protagonists%20the%20principles%20of%20harmonious%20integration%20(Ram)%20and%20analytical%20differentiation%20(Krishna)%2C%20thereby%20grafting%20onto%20the%20two%20avatars%2C%20manifested%20in%20the%20human%20world%2C%20the%20godliness%2C%20the%20divinity%2C%20the%20effulgence%20that%20the%20human%20spirit%20is%20capable%20of%20embodying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20visionary%20poet%20here%20becomes%20synonymous%20with%20the%20Creator%2C%20in%20the%20very%20sense%20meant%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3E%E1%B9%9Agveda%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20address%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20are%20the%20Ocean%2C%20O%20Omniscient%20Poet!%E2%80%9D%20(RV%209%3A86%3A29).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20poet%20is%20able%20to%20bind%20into%20a%20poetic%20structure%20all%20of%20time%20past%20and%20to%20come%2C%20it%20is%20then%20that%20a%20timeless%20epic%20is%20set%20into%20motion.%20In%20our%20literary%20tradition%2C%20time%20is%20the%20soul%20of%20poetry%2C%20and%20its%20metrical%20quality%2C%20its%20music%20is%20what%20creates%20an%20immeasurable%2C%20unbounded%20world%20of%20the%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurely%20there%20is%20something%20special%20in%20the%20character%20of%20Ram%2C%20that%20the%20story%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3ERamayana%3C%2Fem%3E%20flows%20like%20a%20tumbling%20river%20across%20steep%20plateaus%20and%20around%20dense%20jungles%2C%20polishing%20its%20banks%20as%20it%20rushes%20towards%20a%20merger%20with%20the%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20vast%20cultural%20horizon%20of%20India%2C%20is%20there%20any%20region%20untouched%20by%20the%20long-armed%20Ram%3F%20Surely%20it%20is%20on%20account%20of%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20irresistible%20personality%20that%20his%20life-story%20travelled%20across%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20to%20Java%2C%20Sumatra%2C%20Cambodia%20and%20Thailand%2C%20as%20far%20west%20as%20Greece%20and%20as%20far%20east%20as%20Japan%2C%20glittering%20like%20a%20diamond%20necklace%20in%20the%20civilisational%20memories%20of%20the%20lands%20surrounding%20the%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223205%2F800px-WatPhraKeaw_Ramayana_Chariot.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223205%2F800px-WatPhraKeaw_Ramayana_Chariot.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223205%2F800px-WatPhraKeaw_Ramayana_Chariot-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697874%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22532%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EScenes%20from%20the%20Thai%20Ramayana%20at%20a%20temple%20in%20Bangkok.%20Photo%3A%20Jpatokal%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20Public%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20creative%20power%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3ERamayana%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20such%20that%20it%20cannot%20be%20dismissed%20as%20art%20for%20art%E2%80%99s%20sake.%20The%20oeuvre%20of%20the%20first%20poet%2C%20Valmiki%2C%20is%20a%20poetic%20reflection%20of%20the%20luminosity%20inherent%20in%20human%20life.%20His%20epic%20poem%20constitutes%20a%20perfect%20representation%2C%20vividly%20illuminating%20every%20human%20endeavour%20with%20a%20bright%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20know%20that%20there%20are%20two%20ways%20to%20live.%20One%20path%20is%20that%20of%20the%20heart%2C%20of%20faith%20and%20of%20devotion%3B%20the%20other%2C%20that%20of%20the%20ego%2C%20of%20logic%20and%20devoid%20of%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETulsidas%20had%20surrendered%20his%20life%20and%20fate%20to%20Ram.%20Ram%20and%20Ram%20alone%20was%20the%20acme%20of%20his%20faith.%C2%A0When%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20supreme%20deity%2C%20the%20singular%20target%20of%20his%20deepest%20devotion%20and%20his%20complete%20surrender%2C%20for%20Tulsi%20that%20is%20Ram%20and%20only%20Ram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20special%20thing%20about%20surrender%20is%20that%20if%20it%20is%20to%20happen%2C%20when%20it%20happens%2C%20it%20can%20only%20be%20to%20the%20One%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20it%20was%20for%20Tulsidas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%20you%20hear%20clever%20people%20saying%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20dedicating%20themselves%20to%20everyone.%20This%20is%20a%20sly%20way%20of%20avoiding%20the%20question%20of%20the%20One.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20category%20like%20%E2%80%9CHumanity%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20illusion.%20There%20are%20humans%20everywhere.%20Humans%20are%20all%20around%20us.%20Those%20who%20are%20incapable%C2%A0of%C2%A0loving%20one%20single%20human%20being%20say%20that%20they%20love%20all%20of%20humankind%2C%20%E2%80%98Humanity%E2%80%99%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20love%20someone%2C%20another%20human%20being%2C%20you%20have%20to%20leave%20your%20ego%20behind.%20Those%20who%20cannot%20do%20so%20say%20that%20they%20love%20%E2%80%98Humanity%E2%80%99%2C%20because%20they%20know%20that%20%E2%80%98Humanity%E2%80%99%20isn%E2%80%99t%20going%20to%20question%20them%20or%20demand%20anything%20in%20the%20name%20of%20this%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20suffix%20%E2%80%9C-ity%E2%80%9D%20that%20enables%20an%20abstract%20construction%20like%20%E2%80%9CHumanity%E2%80%9D%20is%20very%20convenient.%20It%20allows%20you%20to%C2%A0evade%20the%20responsibility%20that%20comes%20with%20dedicating%20yourself%20to%20the%20One.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ur-Poet%20Valmiki%E2%80%99s%20poem%20has%2024%2C000%20verses%20(%3Cem%3Eshloka%3C%2Fem%3E)%20arranged%20into%20500%20chapters%20(%3Cem%3Esarga%3C%2Fem%3E).%20At%20the%20head%20of%20every%201%2C000%20verses%20stands%20a%20syllable%20of%20the%20Gayatri%20Mantra%2C%20which%20has%2024%20syllables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20different%20styles%20of%20recitation%20%5Bpresumably%20of%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ER%C4%81m%C4%81ya%E1%B9%87a%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20in%20Sanskrit%5D%2C%20northern%20and%20southern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Framayana-versions-poems%5C%22%3ERamayana%20Has%20Many%20Poems%2C%20Many%20Versions%20and%20Many%20Colours%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20ancient%20instance%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CRam%E2%80%9D%20occurs%20in%20the%20Yajurveda%2029%3A59%20%5B%3Cstrong%3ENOTE%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20word%20%E2%80%98r%C4%81ma%E2%80%99%20in%20this%20verse%C2%A0refers%C2%A0to%20a%20pair%20of%20bulls%20with%20specific%20qualities%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20fire-god%20Agni%20and%20the%20sun-god%20Savit%E1%B9%9B%5D.%20Tulsidas%2C%20poet%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3ERamcaritmanas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20has%20also%20taken%20the%20story%20of%20Ram%20to%20be%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20Veda%20and%20thus%20sees%20the%20Ramayana%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Vedic%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20is%20no%20doubt%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20Tulsi%E2%80%99s%20own%20faith%20in%20Ram%20was%20so%20unshakeable%20that%20his%20voice%20became%20transcendent%2C%C2%A0i.e.%2C%20his%20%3Cem%3EManas%3C%2Fem%3E%20transcends%20all%20poetic%20traditions%2C%20whether%20scriptural%2C%20epic%20or%20literary.%20His%20poem%20seems%20to%20come%20from%20knowledge%20that%20is%20pre-conscious%20and%20pre-linguistic%2C%20a%20transcendental%20awareness%20that%20precedes%20conscious%20thought%2C%20language%20and%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%5B%3Cstrong%3ENOTE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20These%20sentences%20refer%20to%20%3Cem%3Epar%C4%81%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Epa%C5%9Byanti%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Emadhyam%C4%81%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Evaikhar%C4%AB%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20four%20levels%20of%20%3Cem%3Ev%C4%81k%3C%2Fem%3E%20(speech)%20theorised%20by%20the%C2%A0classical%C2%A0philosopher%20Bhart%E1%B9%9Bhari.%20In%20describing%20Tulsi%E2%80%99s%20voice%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Epar%C4%81ya%E1%B9%87%C4%AB%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20the%20author%20is%20attributing%20to%20him%20a%20creative%20power%20above%20and%20beyond%20language%20itself%2C%20the%20capacity%20for%20absolute%20poetry%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20212px)%2085vw%2C%20212px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223946%2FTulsidas-212x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22212%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223946%2FTulsidas-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223946%2FTulsidas-723x1024.jpg%20723w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19223946%2FTulsidas.jpg%20847w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697875%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETulsidas.%20Photo%3A%20snl.no.%20Public%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20must%20be%20the%20reason%20that%20the%20authoritative%20literary%20critic%20of%20modern%20Hindi%20letters%2C%20Pandit%20Ram%20Chandra%20Shukla%2C%20has%2C%20in%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHistory%20of%20Hindi%20Literature%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eaccorded%20to%20Tulsidas%E2%80%99s%20oeuvre%20the%20most%20important%20place%20in%20the%20entire%20history%20of%20Hindi%20literary%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETulsidas%20began%20to%20compose%20the%20%3Cem%3ERamcaritmanas%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Ayodhya%20in%C2%A0Samvat%C2%A01631%C2%A0(1574%20CE)%20and%20completed%20his%20epic%20in%20two%20years%20and%20seven%20months.%20It%E2%80%99s%20likely%20that%20some%20of%20it%20was%20written%20in%20Kashi%20(Varanasi).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Professor%20R.C.%20Shukla%2C%20those%20who%20are%20familiar%20with%20Tulsi%E2%80%99s%20languages%20(mainly%20Awadhi%20and%20Braj%20Bhasha)%20can%20tell%20from%20his%20vocabulary%20that%20there%20are%20words%20that%20are%20local%20specifically%20to%C2%A0Chitrakut%C2%A0and%20Ayodhya%2C%20and%20not%20known%20widely%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20great%20critic%20opines%20that%20the%20most%20notable%20feature%20of%20Tulsi%E2%80%99s%20faith%20is%20its%20all-encompassing%20nature%20%E2%80%93%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20neglect%20any%20aspect%20of%20life%2C%20it%20does%20not%20exclude%20anything%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20choose%20one%20side%20over%20the%20other.%20Many%20lines%20converge%20and%20are%20integrated%20within%20the%20poem.%20Thus%20deeds%20(%3Cem%3Ekarma%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20norms%20(%3Cem%3Edharma%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20action%20(karma)%20and%20knowledge%20(%3Cem%3Egyaan%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20all%20these%20oppositions%20are%20reconciled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20critic%20Professor%20Shukla%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20his%20%3Cem%3ERamcaritmanas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20great%20poet%20has%20taken%20devotion%20and%20faith%20to%20be%20much%20more%20efficacious%20and%20rewarding%20than%20knowledge%20as%20means%20to%20our%20desired%20ends.%20We%20find%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3EManas%3C%2Fem%3E%20creative%20skill%2C%20structural%20coherence%2C%20aesthetic%20weight%20and%20so%20on%20%E2%80%93%20every%20exemplary%20literary%20quality%20is%20present%20therein.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20real%20point%20to%20note%20is%20that%20all%20the%20defining%20elements%20of%20a%20narrative%20poem%20are%20both%20equally%20included%20and%20perfectly%20balanced.%20Moreover%2C%20there%20is%20a%20recognition%20on%20the%20poet%E2%80%99s%20part%20of%20the%20crucial%20trigger-points%20in%20the%20story%20(and%20these%20are%20used%20most%20effectively).%20Further%2C%20the%20language%20is%20always%20appropriate%20to%20its%20context%20within%20the%20narrative.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Shukla%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20Tulsidas%20also%20knows%20full%20well%20where%20he%20needs%20to%20deploy%20learned%20idioms%20for%20erudite%20audiences%20and%20where%20the%20occasion%20demands%20everyday%20speech.%20He%20has%20mastered%20how%20to%20work%20the%20erotic%20potential%20(%3Cem%3E%C5%9Bring%C4%81r%20rasa%3C%2Fem%3E)%20of%20his%20story%20in%20such%20a%20way%20as%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20highest%20moral%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20devotion%20to%20Ram%20isn%E2%80%99t%20limited%20to%20serving%20his%20own%20interest%20or%20advertising%20his%20personal%20faith.%20Rather%2C%20he%20wishes%20for%20the%20greater%20common%20good%2C%20looking%20out%20for%20all%20his%20readers%20and%20fellow%20devotees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20Tulsi%E2%80%99s%20time%20and%20thereafter%2C%20Ram%2C%20as%20the%20very%20embodiment%20of%20the%20highest%20virtue%20(%3Cem%3Emary%C4%81d%C4%81%20purushottam%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20became%20a%20people%E2%80%99s%20god%2C%20widely%20revered.%20Valmiki%20was%20the%20first%20to%C2%A0have%20a%20vision%20of%C2%A0Ram%2C%20to%20render%20him%20in%20poetry%2C%20to%20establish%20him%20as%20the%20universal%20ideal%20of%20mankind.%20But%20it%20was%20Tulsi%20who%20really%20took%20him%20to%20the%20masses%2C%20gave%20him%20such%20pride%20of%20place%20in%20popular%20belief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fayodhya-how-would-tulsidas-take-stock-of-the-day-after%5C%22%3EAyodhya%3A%20How%20Would%20Tulsidas%20Take%20Stock%20of%20the%20Day%20After%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20thanks%20to%20the%20epic%20poets%20ancient%20and%20medieval%2C%20Valmiki%20and%20Tulsidas%2C%20that%20the%20story%20of%20Ram%20spread%20gradually%20all%20over%20the%20subcontinent%20and%20even%20beyond%20it%2C%20all%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20sometimes%20the%20poet%20does%20use%20an%20esoteric%20vocabulary.%20By%20%E2%80%98esoteric%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Erahasya-parak%3C%2Fem%3E)%20we%20mean%20a%20kind%20of%20language%20that%20lets%20the%20reader%20know%20that%20she%20isn%E2%80%99t%20exactly%20understanding%20something%2C%20but%20what%20it%20is%20that%20she%20is%20not%20understanding%2C%20that%20she%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20know.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20wonderful%20example%20of%20this%20in%20Tulsidas%E2%80%99s%20Vinay%20Patrika%20(v.%20111)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%B5%2C%C2%A0%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BF%C2%A0%E0%A4%A8%C2%A0%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%87%C2%A0%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%C2%A0%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%8F%E0%A5%A4%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%A4%C2%A0%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%B5%C2%A0%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%C2%A0%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%C2%A0%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF!%C2%A0%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%9D%E0%A4%BF%C2%A0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%82%C2%A0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A8%C2%A0%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%8F%E0%A5%A4%E0%A5%A4%E0%A5%A7%E0%A5%A4%E0%A5%A4%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%C2%A0%E0%A4%AD%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%A4%C2%A0%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%C2%A0%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%2C%C2%A0%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%97%C2%A0%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%82%2C%C2%A0%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%81%C2%A0%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%81%C2%A0%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%BE%C2%A0%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A5%A4%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87%C2%A0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%87%C2%A0%E0%A4%A8%C2%A0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%87%C2%A0%E0%A4%AD%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%2C%C2%A0%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%83%E0%A4%96%C2%A0%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%87%E0%A