%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20say%20it%20is%20real%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20that%20it%20is%20unreal%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20others%20hold%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESays%20Tulsi%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShed%20the%20three%20delusions!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecognise%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20the%20Self.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaith%20is%20an%20overarching%20framework%2C%20a%20supreme%20vision.%20But%20it%20also%20suggests%20a%20kind%20of%20blindness.%20It%E2%80%99s%20when%20we%20cannot%20see%20how%20the%20world%20makes%20sense%2C%20when%20rationality%20fails%20to%20help%20us%20understand%20the%20vagaries%20of%20life%2C%20that%20we%20turn%20to%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDriven%20by%20our%20bewilderment%20in%20the%C2%A0face%20of%C2%A0reality%2C%C2%A0we%20begin%20to%20chant%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20name.%20This%20repetition%20of%20the%20name%20is%20intoxicating%2C%20spell-binding.%20It%20lulls%20us%20into%20forgetting%20both%20our%20troubles%20and%20ourselves.%20Perhaps%20it%20is%20to%20fill%20the%20vacuum%20created%20by%20forgetfulness%20that%20Ram%20appears.%20We%20have%20to%20make%20room%20to%20welcome%20Ram%20into%20our%20life%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20is%20the%20space%20vacated%20by%20our%20ego.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20need%20Ram%20to%20comfort%20and%20anchor%20us%2C%20to%20lodge%20in%20our%20heart%20and%20assuage%C2%A0the%20suffering%20occasioned%20by%20our%20human%20condition%2C%20a%20brilliant%20maverick%20poet%20like%20Kabir%20saw%20through%20the%20kind%20of%20faith%20that%20can%20be%20divisive%2C%20that%20makes%20believers%20overly%20attached%20to%20certain%20symbols%2C%20structures%20and%20rituals%2C%20and%20turns%20them%20against%20the%20followers%20of%20other%C2%A0faiths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKabir%E2%80%99s%20Ram%20had%20no%20form%2C%20no%C2%A0story%20and%C2%A0no%20avatar%3B%20he%20needed%20no%20temple%2C%20no%20idol%20and%20no%20worship.%20For%20Kabir%2C%20Ram%20was%20an%20abstract%20principle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fkabir-in-his-times-and-ours%5C%22%3EKabir%20in%20His%20Time%2C%20And%20Ours%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(%3Cstrong%3ENote%20from%20Ananya%20Vajpeyi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20some%20places%20the%20paragraphs%20have%20been%20rearranged%20for%20greater%20coherence%20and%20flow.%20For%20the%20most%20part%20the%20translation%20hews%20close%20to%20the%20original%20so%20far%20as%20possible%20%E2%80%93%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20naturally%20poetic%20idiom%20and%20his%20resonant%20language%20laden%20with%20imagery%20are%20not%20easy%20to%20bring%20into%20flat%20prose%2C%20quite%20apart%20from%20the%20difficulty%20of%20moving%20from%20Hindi%20to%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20Manish%20Pushkale%20who%20alerted%C2%A0me%20to%20the%20unexpected%20and%20disconcerting%20republication%20of%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20original%20article%20in%20the%20Hindustan%20newspaper%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20special%20supplement%20to%20mark%20the%20ceremonies%20which%20took%C2%A0place%20in%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20at%20Ayodhya%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20Keerthik%20Sasidharan%20who%20made%20the%20Hindi%20text%20available%20to%20me%20and%20encouraged%20me%20to%20translate%20it.%20I%E2%80%99m%20grateful%20to%20Philip%20Lutgendorf%20and%20Akhilesh%20Mani%20Shandilya%20with%20whom%20I%2C%20along%20with%20my%20colleagues%2C%20was%20able%20to%20discuss%20Tulsidas%20in%20the%20winter%20of%202023-24%2C%20and%20to%20Linda%20Hess%20and%20Purushottam%20Agrawal%20from%20whom%20I%20keep%20on%20learning%20about%20Kabir).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKailash%C2%A0Vajpeyi%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%20(1936-2015)%20was%20a%20poet%2C%20scholar%2C%20broadcaster%20and%20public%20intellectual%20who%20wrote%20extensively%20in%20Hindi%20and%20English.%20He%20received%20many%20literary%20awards%20and%20his%20work%20is%20translated%20into%20many%20languages.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%